var book = {
	"name": "2 Chronicles",
	"numChapters": 36,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Solomon son of David established<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11196C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11196C\"></sup> himself firmly over his kingdom, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God was with<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11196D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11196D\"></sup> him and made him exceedingly great.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11196E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11196E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Solomon spoke to all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11197F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11197F\"></sup>—to the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds, to the judges and to all the leaders in Israel, the heads of families—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and Solomon and the whole assembly went to the high place at Gibeon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11198G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11198G\"></sup> for God’s tent of meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11198H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11198H\"></sup> was there, which Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11198I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11198I\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s servant had made in the wilderness.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now David had brought up the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11199J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11199J\"></sup> of God from Kiriath Jearim to the place he had prepared for it, because he had pitched a tent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11199K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11199K\"></sup> for it in Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the bronze altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11200L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11200L\"></sup> that Bezalel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11200M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11200M\"></sup> son of Uri, the son of Hur, had made was in Gibeon in front of the tabernacle of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; so Solomon and the assembly inquired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11200N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11200N\"></sup> of him there.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Solomon went up to the bronze altar before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the tent of meeting and offered a thousand burnt offerings on it.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>That night God appeared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11202O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11202O\"></sup> to Solomon and said to him, “Ask for whatever you want me to give you.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Solomon answered God, “You have shown great kindness to David my father and have made me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11203P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11203P\"></sup> king in his place.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, let your promise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11204Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11204Q\"></sup> to my father David be confirmed, for you have made me king over a people who are as numerous as the dust of the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11204R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11204R\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Give me wisdom and knowledge, that I may lead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11205S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11205S\"></sup> this people, for who is able to govern this great people of yours?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>God said to Solomon, “Since this is your heart’s desire and you have not asked for wealth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11206T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11206T\"></sup> possessions or honor, nor for the death of your enemies, and since you have not asked for a long life but for wisdom and knowledge to govern my people over whom I have made you king,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>therefore wisdom and knowledge will be given you. And I will also give you wealth, possessions and honor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11207U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11207U\"></sup> such as no king who was before you ever had and none after you will have.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11207V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11207V\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Solomon went to Jerusalem from the high place at Gibeon, from before the tent of meeting. And he reigned over Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Solomon accumulated chariots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11209W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11209W\"></sup> and horses; he had fourteen hundred chariots and twelve thousand horses, which he kept in the chariot cities and also with him in Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The king made silver and gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11210X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11210X\"></sup> as common in Jerusalem as stones, and cedar as plentiful as sycamore-fig trees in the foothills.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Solomon’s horses were imported from Egypt and from Kue—the royal merchants purchased them from Kue at the current price.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They imported a chariot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11212Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11212Y\"></sup> from Egypt for six hundred shekels of silver, and a horse for a hundred and fifty. They also exported them to all the kings of the Hittites and of the Arameans."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Solomon gave orders to build a temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11213B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11213B\"></sup> for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and a royal palace for himself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11213C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11213C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He conscripted 70,000 men as carriers and 80,000 as stonecutters in the hills and 3,600 as foremen over them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11214D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11214D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Solomon sent this message to Hiram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11215E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11215E\"></sup> king of Tyre:“Send me cedar logs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11215F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11215F\"></sup> as you did for my father David when you sent him cedar to build a palace to live in.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now I am about to build a temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11216G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11216G\"></sup> for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God and to dedicate it to him for burning fragrant incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11216H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11216H\"></sup> before him, for setting out the consecrated bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11216I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11216I\"></sup> regularly, and for making burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11216J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11216J\"></sup> every morning and evening and on the Sabbaths,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11216K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11216K\"></sup> at the New Moons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11216L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11216L\"></sup> and at the appointed festivals of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God. This is a lasting ordinance for Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“The temple I am going to build will be great,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11217M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11217M\"></sup> because our God is greater than all other gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11217N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11217N\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But who is able to build a temple for him, since the heavens, even the highest heavens, cannot contain him?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11218O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11218O\"></sup> Who then am I<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11218P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11218P\"></sup> to build a temple for him, except as a place to burn sacrifices before him?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Send me, therefore, a man skilled to work in gold and silver, bronze and iron, and in purple, crimson and blue yarn, and experienced in the art of engraving, to work in Judah and Jerusalem with my skilled workers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11219Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11219Q\"></sup> whom my father David provided.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Send me also cedar, juniper and algum logs from Lebanon, for I know that your servants are skilled in cutting timber there. My servants will work with yours",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>to provide me with plenty of lumber, because the temple I build must be large and magnificent.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I will give your servants, the woodsmen who cut the timber, twenty thousand cors of ground wheat, twenty thousand cors of barley, twenty thousand baths of wine and twenty thousand baths of olive oil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11222R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11222R\"></sup>”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Hiram king of Tyre replied by letter to Solomon:“Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11223S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11223S\"></sup> his people, he has made you their king.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Hiram added:“Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who made heaven and earth!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11224T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11224T\"></sup> He has given King David a wise son, endowed with intelligence and discernment, who will build a temple for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and a palace for himself.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“I am sending you Huram-Abi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11225U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11225U\"></sup> a man of great skill,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>whose mother was from Dan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11226V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11226V\"></sup> and whose father was from Tyre. He is trained<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11226W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11226W\"></sup> to work in gold and silver, bronze and iron, stone and wood, and with purple and blue<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11226X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11226X\"></sup> and crimson yarn and fine linen. He is experienced in all kinds of engraving and can execute any design given to him. He will work with your skilled workers and with those of my lord, David your father.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Now let my lord send his servants the wheat and barley and the olive oil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11227Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11227Y\"></sup> and wine he promised,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and we will cut all the logs from Lebanon that you need and will float them as rafts by sea down to Joppa.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11228Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11228Z\"></sup> You can then take them up to Jerusalem.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Solomon took a census of all the foreigners<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11229AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11229AA\"></sup> residing in Israel, after the census<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11229AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11229AB\"></sup> his father David had taken; and they were found to be 153,600.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He assigned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11230AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11230AC\"></sup> 70,000 of them to be carriers and 80,000 to be stonecutters in the hills, with 3,600 foremen over them to keep the people working."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Then Solomon began to build<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11231B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11231B\"></sup> the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11231C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11231C\"></sup> in Jerusalem on Mount Moriah, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had appeared to his father David. It was on the threshing floor of Araunah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11231D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11231D\"></sup> the Jebusite, the place provided by David.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He began building on the second day of the second month in the fourth year of his reign.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11232E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11232E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The foundation Solomon laid for building the temple of God was sixty cubits long and twenty cubits wide<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11233F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11233F\"></sup> (using the cubit of the old standard).",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The portico at the front of the temple was twenty cubits long across the width of the building and twenty cubits high.He overlaid the inside with pure gold.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He paneled the main hall with juniper and covered it with fine gold and decorated it with palm tree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11235G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11235G\"></sup> and chain designs.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He adorned the temple with precious stones. And the gold he used was gold of Parvaim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He overlaid the ceiling beams, doorframes, walls and doors of the temple with gold, and he carved cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11237H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11237H\"></sup> on the walls.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He built the Most Holy Place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11238I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11238I\"></sup> its length corresponding to the width of the temple—twenty cubits long and twenty cubits wide. He overlaid the inside with six hundred talents of fine gold.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The gold nails<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11239J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11239J\"></sup> weighed fifty shekels. He also overlaid the upper parts with gold.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For the Most Holy Place he made a pair<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11240K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11240K\"></sup> of sculptured cherubim and overlaid them with gold.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The total wingspan of the cherubim was twenty cubits. One wing of the first cherub was five cubits long and touched the temple wall, while its other wing, also five cubits long, touched the wing of the other cherub.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Similarly one wing of the second cherub was five cubits long and touched the other temple wall, and its other wing, also five cubits long, touched the wing of the first cherub.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The wings of these cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11243L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11243L\"></sup> extended twenty cubits. They stood on their feet, facing the main hall.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He made the curtain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11244M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11244M\"></sup> of blue, purple and crimson yarn and fine linen, with cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11244N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11244N\"></sup> worked into it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For the front of the temple he made two pillars,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11245O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11245O\"></sup> which together were thirty-five cubits long, each with a capital<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11245P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11245P\"></sup> five cubits high.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He made interwoven chains<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11246Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11246Q\"></sup> and put them on top of the pillars. He also made a hundred pomegranates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11246R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11246R\"></sup> and attached them to the chains.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He erected the pillars in the front of the temple, one to the south and one to the north. The one to the south he named Jakin and the one to the north Boaz."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>He made a bronze altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11248B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11248B\"></sup> twenty cubits long, twenty cubits wide and ten cubits high.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He made the Sea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11249C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11249C\"></sup> of cast metal, circular in shape, measuring ten cubits from rim to rim and five cubits high. It took a line of thirty cubits to measure around it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Below the rim, figures of bulls encircled it—ten to a cubit. The bulls were cast in two rows in one piece with the Sea.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Sea stood on twelve bulls, three facing north, three facing west, three facing south and three facing east.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11251D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11251D\"></sup> The Sea rested on top of them, and their hindquarters were toward the center.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It was a handbreadth in thickness, and its rim was like the rim of a cup, like a lily blossom. It held three thousand baths.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He then made ten basins<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11253E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11253E\"></sup> for washing and placed five on the south side and five on the north. In them the things to be used for the burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11253F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11253F\"></sup> were rinsed, but the Sea was to be used by the priests for washing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He made ten gold lampstands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11254G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11254G\"></sup> according to the specifications<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11254H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11254H\"></sup> for them and placed them in the temple, five on the south side and five on the north.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He made ten tables<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11255I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11255I\"></sup> and placed them in the temple, five on the south side and five on the north. He also made a hundred gold sprinkling bowls.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11255J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11255J\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He made the courtyard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11256K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11256K\"></sup> of the priests, and the large court and the doors for the court, and overlaid the doors with bronze.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He placed the Sea on the south side, at the southeast corner.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Huram also made the pots and shovels and sprinkling bowls.So Huram finished<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11258L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11258L\"></sup> the work he had undertaken for King Solomon in the temple of God:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the two pillars;the two bowl-shaped capitals on top of the pillars;the two sets of network decorating the two bowl-shaped capitals on top of the pillars;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the four hundred pomegranates for the two sets of network (two rows of pomegranates for each network, decorating the bowl-shaped capitals on top of the pillars);",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the stands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11261M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11261M\"></sup> with their basins;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the Sea and the twelve bulls under it;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the pots, shovels, meat forks and all related articles.All the objects that Huram-Abi<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11263N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11263N\"></sup> made for King Solomon for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> were of polished bronze.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king had them cast in clay molds in the plain of the Jordan between Sukkoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11264O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11264O\"></sup> and Zarethan.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>All these things that Solomon made amounted to so much that the weight of the bronze<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11265P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11265P\"></sup> could not be calculated.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Solomon also made all the furnishings that were in God’s temple:the golden altar;the tables<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11266Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11266Q\"></sup> on which was the bread of the Presence;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the lampstands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11267R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11267R\"></sup> of pure gold with their lamps, to burn in front of the inner sanctuary as prescribed;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>the gold floral work and lamps and tongs (they were solid gold);",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>the pure gold wick trimmers, sprinkling bowls, dishes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11269S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11269S\"></sup> and censers;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11269T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11269T\"></sup> and the gold doors of the temple: the inner doors to the Most Holy Place and the doors of the main hall."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>When all the work Solomon had done for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was finished,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11270A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11270A\"></sup> he brought in the things his father David had dedicated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11270B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11270B\"></sup>—the silver and gold and all the furnishings—and he placed them in the treasuries of God’s temple.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Solomon summoned to Jerusalem the elders of Israel, all the heads of the tribes and the chiefs of the Israelite families, to bring up the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11271D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11271D\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s covenant from Zion, the City of David.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And all the Israelites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11272E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11272E\"></sup> came together to the king at the time of the festival in the seventh month.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When all the elders of Israel had arrived, the Levites took up the ark,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and they brought up the ark and the tent of meeting and all the sacred furnishings in it. The Levitical priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11274F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11274F\"></sup> carried them up;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and King Solomon and the entire assembly of Israel that had gathered about him were before the ark, sacrificing so many sheep and cattle that they could not be recorded or counted.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The priests then brought the ark<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11276G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11276G\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s covenant to its place in the inner sanctuary of the temple, the Most Holy Place, and put it beneath the wings of the cherubim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The cherubim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11277H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11277H\"></sup> spread their wings over the place of the ark and covered the ark and its carrying poles.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>These poles were so long that their ends, extending from the ark, could be seen from in front of the inner sanctuary, but not from outside the Holy Place; and they are still there today.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>There was nothing in the ark except<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11279I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11279I\"></sup> the two tablets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11279J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11279J\"></sup> that Moses had placed in it at Horeb, where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with the Israelites after they came out of Egypt.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The priests then withdrew from the Holy Place. All the priests who were there had consecrated themselves, regardless of their divisions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11280K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11280K\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>All the Levites who were musicians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11281L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11281L\"></sup>—Asaph, Heman, Jeduthun and their sons and relatives—stood on the east side of the altar, dressed in fine linen and playing cymbals, harps and lyres. They were accompanied by 120 priests sounding trumpets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11281M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11281M\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The trumpeters and musicians joined in unison to give praise and thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Accompanied by trumpets, cymbals and other instruments, the singers raised their voices in praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and sang:“He is good;his love endures forever.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11282N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11282N\"></sup>Then the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was filled with the cloud,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11282O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11282O\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and the priests could not perform<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11283P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11283P\"></sup> their service because of the cloud,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11283Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11283Q\"></sup> for the glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11283R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11283R\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the temple of God."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Then Solomon said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has said that he would dwell in a dark cloud;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11284A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11284A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I have built a magnificent temple for you, a place for you to dwell forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11285B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11285B\"></sup>”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>While the whole assembly of Israel was standing there, the king turned around and blessed them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then he said:“Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, who with his hands has fulfilled what he promised with his mouth to my father David. For he said,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘Since the day I brought my people out of Egypt, I have not chosen a city in any tribe of Israel to have a temple built so that my Name might be there, nor have I chosen anyone to be ruler over my people Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But now I have chosen Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11289C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11289C\"></sup> for my Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11289D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11289D\"></sup> to be there, and I have chosen David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11289E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11289E\"></sup> to rule my people Israel.’",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“My father David had it in his heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11290F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11290F\"></sup> to build a temple for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to my father David, ‘You did well to have it in your heart to build a temple for my Name.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Nevertheless, you are not the one to build the temple, but your son, your own flesh and blood—he is the one who will build the temple for my Name.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has kept the promise he made. I have succeeded David my father and now I sit on the throne of Israel, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised, and I have built the temple for the Name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>There I have placed the ark, in which is the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11294G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11294G\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he made with the people of Israel.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Solomon stood before the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in front of the whole assembly of Israel and spread out his hands.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now he had made a bronze platform,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11296J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11296J\"></sup> five cubits long, five cubits wide and three cubits high, and had placed it in the center of the outer court. He stood on the platform and then knelt down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11296K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11296K\"></sup> before the whole assembly of Israel and spread out his hands toward heaven.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said:“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, there is no God like you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11297L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11297L\"></sup> in heaven or on earth—you who keep your covenant of love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11297M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11297M\"></sup> with your servants who continue wholeheartedly in your way.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You have kept your promise to your servant David my father; with your mouth you have promised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11298N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11298N\"></sup> and with your hand you have fulfilled it—as it is today.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, keep for your servant David my father the promises you made to him when you said, ‘You shall never fail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11299O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11299O\"></sup> to have a successor to sit before me on the throne of Israel, if only your descendants are careful in all they do to walk before me according to my law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11299P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11299P\"></sup> as you have done.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And now, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, let your word that you promised your servant David come true.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“But will God really dwell<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11301Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11301Q\"></sup> on earth with humans? The heavens,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11301R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11301R\"></sup> even the highest heavens, cannot contain you. How much less this temple I have built!",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Yet, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God, give attention to your servant’s prayer and his plea for mercy. Hear the cry and the prayer that your servant is praying in your presence.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>May your eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11303S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11303S\"></sup> be open toward this temple day and night, this place of which you said you would put your Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11303T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11303T\"></sup> there. May you hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11303U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11303U\"></sup> the prayer your servant prays toward this place.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Hear the supplications of your servant and of your people Israel when they pray toward this place. Hear from heaven, your dwelling place; and when you hear, forgive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11304V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11304V\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“When anyone wrongs their neighbor and is required to take an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11305W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11305W\"></sup> and they come and swear the oath before your altar in this temple,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then hear from heaven and act. Judge between your servants, condemning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11306X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11306X\"></sup> the guilty and bringing down on their heads what they have done, and vindicating the innocent by treating them in accordance with their innocence.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“When your people Israel have been defeated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11307Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11307Y\"></sup> by an enemy because they have sinned against you and when they turn back and give praise to your name, praying and making supplication before you in this temple,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of your people Israel and bring them back to the land you gave to them and their ancestors.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“When the heavens are shut up and there is no rain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11309Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11309Z\"></sup> because your people have sinned against you, and when they pray toward this place and give praise to your name and turn from their sin because you have afflicted them,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>then hear from heaven and forgive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11310AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11310AA\"></sup> the sin of your servants, your people Israel. Teach them the right way to live, and send rain on the land you gave your people for an inheritance.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“When famine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11311AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11311AB\"></sup> or plague comes to the land, or blight or mildew, locusts or grasshoppers, or when enemies besiege them in any of their cities, whatever disaster or disease may come,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and when a prayer or plea is made by anyone among your people Israel—being aware of their afflictions and pains, and spreading out their hands toward this temple—",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>then hear from heaven, your dwelling place. Forgive,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11313AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11313AC\"></sup> and deal with everyone according to all they do, since you know their hearts (for you alone know the human heart),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11313AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11313AD\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>so that they will fear you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11314AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11314AE\"></sup> and walk in obedience to you all the time they live in the land you gave our ancestors.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“As for the foreigner who does not belong to your people Israel but has come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11315AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11315AF\"></sup> from a distant land because of your great name and your mighty hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11315AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11315AG\"></sup> and your outstretched arm—when they come and pray toward this temple,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>then hear from heaven, your dwelling place. Do whatever the foreigner<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11316AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11316AH\"></sup> asks of you, so that all the peoples of the earth may know your name and fear you, as do your own people Israel, and may know that this house I have built bears your Name.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“When your people go to war against their enemies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11317AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11317AI\"></sup> wherever you send them, and when they pray<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11317AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11317AJ\"></sup> to you toward this city you have chosen and the temple I have built for your Name,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>then hear from heaven their prayer and their plea, and uphold their cause.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“When they sin against you—for there is no one who does not sin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11319AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11319AK\"></sup>—and you become angry with them and give them over to the enemy, who takes them captive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11319AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11319AL\"></sup> to a land far away or near;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and if they have a change of heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11320AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11320AM\"></sup> in the land where they are held captive, and repent and plead with you in the land of their captivity and say, ‘We have sinned, we have done wrong and acted wickedly’;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and if they turn back to you with all their heart and soul in the land of their captivity where they were taken, and pray toward the land you gave their ancestors, toward the city you have chosen and toward the temple I have built for your Name;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>then from heaven, your dwelling place, hear their prayer and their pleas, and uphold their cause. And forgive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11322AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11322AN\"></sup> your people, who have sinned against you.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“Now, my God, may your eyes be open and your ears attentive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11323AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11323AO\"></sup> to the prayers offered in this place.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“Now arise,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11324AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11324AP\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, and come to your resting place,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11324AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11324AQ\"></sup>you and the ark of your might.May your priests,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11324AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11324AR\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, be clothed with salvation,may your faithful people rejoice in your goodness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11324AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11324AS\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, do not reject your anointed one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11325AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11325AT\"></sup>Remember the great love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11325AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11325AU\"></sup> promised to David your servant.”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>When Solomon finished praying, fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11326B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11326B\"></sup> came down from heaven and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices, and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11326C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11326C\"></sup> the temple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11326D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11326D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The priests could not enter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11327E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11327E\"></sup> the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because the glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11327F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11327F\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When all the Israelites saw the fire coming down and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> above the temple, they knelt on the pavement with their faces to the ground, and they worshiped and gave thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying,“He is good;his love endures forever.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11328G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11328G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king and all the people offered sacrifices before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And King Solomon offered a sacrifice of twenty-two thousand head of cattle and a hundred and twenty thousand sheep and goats. So the king and all the people dedicated the temple of God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The priests took their positions, as did the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11331H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11331H\"></sup> with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s musical instruments,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11331I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11331I\"></sup> which King David had made for praising the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and which were used when he gave thanks, saying, “His love endures forever.” Opposite the Levites, the priests blew their trumpets, and all the Israelites were standing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Solomon consecrated the middle part of the courtyard in front of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and there he offered burnt offerings and the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11332J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11332J\"></sup> of the fellowship offerings, because the bronze altar he had made could not hold the burnt offerings, the grain offerings and the fat portions.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Solomon observed the festival<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11333K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11333K\"></sup> at that time for seven days, and all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11333L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11333L\"></sup> with him—a vast assembly, people from Lebo Hamath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11333M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11333M\"></sup> to the Wadi of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11333N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11333N\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>On the eighth day they held an assembly, for they had celebrated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11334O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11334O\"></sup> the dedication of the altar for seven days and the festival<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11334P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11334P\"></sup> for seven days more.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>On the twenty-third day of the seventh month he sent the people to their homes, joyful and glad in heart for the good things the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done for David and Solomon and for his people Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When Solomon had finished<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11336R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11336R\"></sup> the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the royal palace, and had succeeded in carrying out all he had in mind to do in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in his own palace,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11337S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11337S\"></sup> to him at night and said:“I have heard your prayer and have chosen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11337T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11337T\"></sup> this place for myself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11337U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11337U\"></sup> as a temple for sacrifices.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“When I shut up the heavens so that there is no rain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11338V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11338V\"></sup> or command locusts to devour the land or send a plague among my people,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>if my people, who are called by my name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11339W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11339W\"></sup> will humble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11339X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11339X\"></sup> themselves and pray and seek my face<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11339Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11339Y\"></sup> and turn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11339Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11339Z\"></sup> from their wicked ways, then I will hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11339AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11339AA\"></sup> from heaven, and I will forgive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11339AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11339AB\"></sup> their sin and will heal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11339AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11339AC\"></sup> their land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now my eyes will be open and my ears attentive to the prayers offered in this place.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11340AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11340AD\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I have chosen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11341AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11341AE\"></sup> and consecrated this temple so that my Name may be there forever. My eyes and my heart will always be there.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“As for you, if you walk before me faithfully<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11342AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11342AF\"></sup> as David your father did, and do all I command, and observe my decrees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11342AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11342AG\"></sup> and laws,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I will establish your royal throne, as I covenanted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11343AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11343AH\"></sup> with David your father when I said, ‘You shall never fail to have a successor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11343AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11343AI\"></sup> to rule over Israel.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11343AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11343AJ\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“But if you turn away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11344AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11344AK\"></sup> and forsake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11344AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11344AL\"></sup> the decrees and commands I have given you and go off to serve other gods and worship them,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>then I will uproot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11345AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11345AM\"></sup> Israel from my land,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11345AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11345AN\"></sup> which I have given them, and will reject this temple I have consecrated for my Name. I will make it a byword and an object of ridicule<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11345AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11345AO\"></sup> among all peoples.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>This temple will become a heap of rubble. All who pass by will be appalled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11346AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11346AP\"></sup> and say,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11346AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11346AQ\"></sup> ‘Why has the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> done such a thing to this land and to this temple?’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>People will answer, ‘Because they have forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors, who brought them out of Egypt, and have embraced other gods, worshiping and serving them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11347AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11347AR\"></sup>—that is why he brought all this disaster on them.’”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>At the end of twenty years, during which Solomon built the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his own palace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11348B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11348B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Solomon rebuilt the villages that Hiram had given him, and settled Israelites in them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Solomon then went to Hamath Zobah and captured it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He also built up Tadmor in the desert and all the store cities he had built in Hamath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11351C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11351C\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He rebuilt Upper Beth Horon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11352D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11352D\"></sup> and Lower Beth Horon as fortified cities, with walls and with gates and bars,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>as well as Baalath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11353E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11353E\"></sup> and all his store cities, and all the cities for his chariots and for his horses—whatever he desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon and throughout all the territory he ruled.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>There were still people left from the Hittites, Amorites, Perizzites, Hivites and Jebusites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11354F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11354F\"></sup> (these people were not Israelites).",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Solomon conscripted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11355G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11355G\"></sup> the descendants of all these people remaining in the land—whom the Israelites had not destroyed—to serve as slave labor, as it is to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Solomon did not make slaves of the Israelites for his work; they were his fighting men, commanders of his captains, and commanders of his chariots and charioteers.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They were also King Solomon’s chief officials—two hundred and fifty officials supervising the men.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Solomon brought Pharaoh’s daughter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11358H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11358H\"></sup> up from the City of David to the palace he had built for her, for he said, “My wife must not live in the palace of David king of Israel, because the places the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has entered are holy.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>On the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11359I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11359I\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that he had built in front of the portico, Solomon sacrificed burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>according to the daily requirement<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11360J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11360J\"></sup> for offerings commanded by Moses for the Sabbaths,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11360K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11360K\"></sup> the New Moons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11360L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11360L\"></sup> and the three<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11360M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11360M\"></sup> annual festivals—the Festival of Unleavened Bread,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11360N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11360N\"></sup> the Festival of Weeks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11360O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11360O\"></sup> and the Festival of Tabernacles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11360P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11360P\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In keeping with the ordinance of his father David, he appointed the divisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11361Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11361Q\"></sup> of the priests for their duties, and the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11361R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11361R\"></sup> to lead the praise and to assist the priests according to each day’s requirement. He also appointed the gatekeepers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11361S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11361S\"></sup> by divisions for the various gates, because this was what David the man of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11361T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11361T\"></sup> had ordered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11361U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11361U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They did not deviate from the king’s commands to the priests or to the Levites in any matter, including that of the treasuries.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All Solomon’s work was carried out, from the day the foundation of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was laid until its completion. So the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was finished.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Solomon went to Ezion Geber and Elath on the coast of Edom.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Hiram sent him ships commanded by his own men, sailors who knew the sea. These, with Solomon’s men, sailed to Ophir and brought back four hundred and fifty talents of gold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11365V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11365V\"></sup> which they delivered to King Solomon."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>When the queen of Sheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11366B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11366B\"></sup> heard of Solomon’s fame, she came to Jerusalem to test him with hard questions. Arriving with a very great caravan—with camels carrying spices, large quantities of gold, and precious stones—she came to Solomon and talked with him about all she had on her mind.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Solomon answered all her questions; nothing was too hard for him to explain to her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the queen of Sheba saw the wisdom of Solomon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11368C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11368C\"></sup> as well as the palace he had built,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the food on his table, the seating of his officials, the attending servants in their robes, the cupbearers in their robes and the burnt offerings he made at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, she was overwhelmed.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>She said to the king, “The report I heard in my own country about your achievements and your wisdom is true.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But I did not believe what they said until I came<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11371D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11371D\"></sup> and saw with my own eyes. Indeed, not even half the greatness of your wisdom was told me; you have far exceeded the report I heard.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>How happy your people must be! How happy your officials, who continually stand before you and hear your wisdom!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has delighted in you and placed you on his throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11373E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11373E\"></sup> as king to rule for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. Because of the love of your God for Israel and his desire to uphold them forever, he has made you king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11373F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11373F\"></sup> over them, to maintain justice and righteousness.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then she gave the king 120 talents of gold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11374G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11374G\"></sup> large quantities of spices, and precious stones. There had never been such spices as those the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>(The servants of Hiram and the servants of Solomon brought gold from Ophir;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11375H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11375H\"></sup> they also brought algumwood and precious stones.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The king used the algumwood to make steps for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for the royal palace, and to make harps and lyres for the musicians. Nothing like them had ever been seen in Judah.)",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>King Solomon gave the queen of Sheba all she desired and asked for; he gave her more than she had brought to him. Then she left and returned with her retinue to her own country.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The weight of the gold that Solomon received yearly was 666 talents,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>not including the revenues brought in by merchants and traders. Also all the kings of Arabia<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11379J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11379J\"></sup> and the governors of the territories brought gold and silver to Solomon.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>King Solomon made two hundred large shields of hammered gold; six hundred shekels of hammered gold went into each shield.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He also made three hundred small shields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11381K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11381K\"></sup> of hammered gold, with three hundred shekels of gold in each shield. The king put them in the Palace of the Forest of Lebanon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11381L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11381L\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the king made a great throne covered with ivory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11382M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11382M\"></sup> and overlaid with pure gold.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The throne had six steps, and a footstool of gold was attached to it. On both sides of the seat were armrests, with a lion standing beside each of them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Twelve lions stood on the six steps, one at either end of each step. Nothing like it had ever been made for any other kingdom.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All King Solomon’s goblets were gold, and all the household articles in the Palace of the Forest of Lebanon were pure gold. Nothing was made of silver, because silver was considered of little value in Solomon’s day.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king had a fleet of trading ships manned by Hiram’s servants. Once every three years it returned, carrying gold, silver and ivory, and apes and baboons.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>King Solomon was greater in riches and wisdom than all the other kings of the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11387N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11387N\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>All the kings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11388O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11388O\"></sup> of the earth sought audience with Solomon to hear the wisdom God had put in his heart.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Year after year, everyone who came brought a gift<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11389P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11389P\"></sup>—articles of silver and gold, and robes, weapons and spices, and horses and mules.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Solomon had four thousand stalls for horses and chariots,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11390Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11390Q\"></sup> and twelve thousand horses, which he kept in the chariot cities and also with him in Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He ruled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11391R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11391R\"></sup> over all the kings from the Euphrates River<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11391S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11391S\"></sup> to the land of the Philistines, as far as the border of Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11391T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11391T\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stones, and cedar as plentiful as sycamore-fig trees in the foothills.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Solomon’s horses were imported from Egypt and from all other countries.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As for the other events of Solomon’s reign, from beginning to end, are they not written in the records of Nathan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11394V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11394V\"></sup> the prophet, in the prophecy of Ahijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11394W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11394W\"></sup> the Shilonite and in the visions of Iddo the seer concerning Jeroboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11394X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11394X\"></sup> son of Nebat?",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he rested with his ancestors and was buried in the city of David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11396Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11396Y\"></sup> his father. And Rehoboam his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had gone there to make him king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Jeroboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11398B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11398B\"></sup> son of Nebat heard this (he was in Egypt, where he had fled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11398C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11398C\"></sup> from King Solomon), he returned from Egypt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So they sent for Jeroboam, and he and all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11399D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11399D\"></sup> went to Rehoboam and said to him:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Your father put a heavy yoke on us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11400E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11400E\"></sup> but now lighten the harsh labor and the heavy yoke he put on us, and we will serve you.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Rehoboam answered, “Come back to me in three days.” So the people went away.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Rehoboam consulted the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11402F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11402F\"></sup> who had served his father Solomon during his lifetime. “How would you advise me to answer these people?” he asked.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They replied, “If you will be kind to these people and please them and give them a favorable answer,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11403G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11403G\"></sup> they will always be your servants.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Rehoboam rejected<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11404H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11404H\"></sup> the advice the elders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11404I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11404I\"></sup> gave him and consulted the young men who had grown up with him and were serving him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He asked them, “What is your advice? How should we answer these people who say to me, ‘Lighten the yoke your father put on us’?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The young men who had grown up with him replied, “The people have said to you, ‘Your father put a heavy yoke on us, but make our yoke lighter.’ Now tell them, ‘My little finger is thicker than my father’s waist.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My father laid on you a heavy yoke; I will make it even heavier. My father scourged you with whips; I will scourge you with scorpions.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Three days later Jeroboam and all the people returned to Rehoboam, as the king had said, “Come back to me in three days.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king answered them harshly. Rejecting the advice of the elders,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>he followed the advice of the young men and said, “My father made your yoke heavy; I will make it even heavier. My father scourged you with whips; I will scourge you with scorpions.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the king did not listen to the people, for this turn of events was from God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11411J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11411J\"></sup> to fulfill the word the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to Jeroboam son of Nebat through Ahijah the Shilonite.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11411K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11411K\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11412L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11412L\"></sup> saw that the king refused to listen to them, they answered the king:“What share do we have in David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11412M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11412M\"></sup>what part in Jesse’s son?To your tents, Israel!Look after your own house, David!”So all the Israelites went home.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But as for the Israelites who were living in the towns of Judah, Rehoboam still ruled over them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>King Rehoboam sent out Adoniram,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11414N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11414N\"></sup> who was in charge of forced labor, but the Israelites stoned him to death. King Rehoboam, however, managed to get into his chariot and escape to Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>When Rehoboam arrived in Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11416A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11416A\"></sup> he mustered Judah and Benjamin—a hundred and eighty thousand able young men—to go to war against Israel and to regain the kingdom for Rehoboam.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But this word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Shemaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11417B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11417B\"></sup> the man of God:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Say to Rehoboam son of Solomon king of Judah and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: Do not go up to fight against your fellow Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11419C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11419C\"></sup> Go home, every one of you, for this is my doing.’” So they obeyed the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and turned back from marching against Jeroboam.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Rehoboam lived in Jerusalem and built up towns for defense in Judah:",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Beth Zur, Soko, Adullam,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Gath, Mareshah, Ziph,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Zorah, Aijalon and Hebron. These were fortified cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11425D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11425D\"></sup> in Judah and Benjamin.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He strengthened their defenses and put commanders in them, with supplies of food, olive oil and wine.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He put shields and spears in all the cities, and made them very strong. So Judah and Benjamin were his.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The priests and Levites from all their districts throughout Israel sided with him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11429E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11429E\"></sup> even abandoned their pasturelands and property<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11429F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11429F\"></sup> and came to Judah and Jerusalem, because Jeroboam and his sons had rejected them as priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>when he appointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11430G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11430G\"></sup> his own priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11430H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11430H\"></sup> for the high places and for the goat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11430I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11430I\"></sup> and calf<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11430J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11430J\"></sup> idols he had made.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Those from every tribe of Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11431K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11431K\"></sup> who set their hearts on seeking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, followed the Levites to Jerusalem to offer sacrifices to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They strengthened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11432L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11432L\"></sup> the kingdom of Judah and supported Rehoboam son of Solomon three years, following the ways of David and Solomon during this time.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Rehoboam married Mahalath, who was the daughter of David’s son Jerimoth and of Abihail, the daughter of Jesse’s son Eliab.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>She bore him sons: Jeush, Shemariah and Zaham.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then he married Maakah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11435M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11435M\"></sup> daughter of Absalom, who bore him Abijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11435N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11435N\"></sup> Attai, Ziza and Shelomith.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Rehoboam loved Maakah daughter of Absalom more than any of his other wives and concubines. In all, he had eighteen wives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11436O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11436O\"></sup> and sixty concubines, twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Rehoboam appointed Abijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11437P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11437P\"></sup> son of Maakah as crown prince among his brothers, in order to make him king.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He acted wisely, dispersing some of his sons throughout the districts of Judah and Benjamin, and to all the fortified cities. He gave them abundant provisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11438Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11438Q\"></sup> and took many wives for them."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>After Rehoboam’s position as king was established<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11439B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11439B\"></sup> and he had become strong,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11439C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11439C\"></sup> he and all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11439D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11439D\"></sup> with him abandoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11439E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11439E\"></sup> the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Because they had been unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11440F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11440F\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Shishak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11440G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11440G\"></sup> king of Egypt attacked Jerusalem in the fifth year of King Rehoboam.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>With twelve hundred chariots and sixty thousand horsemen and the innumerable troops of Libyans,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11441H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11441H\"></sup> Sukkites and Cushites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11441I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11441I\"></sup> that came with him from Egypt,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>he captured the fortified cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11442J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11442J\"></sup> of Judah and came as far as Jerusalem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the prophet Shemaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11443K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11443K\"></sup> came to Rehoboam and to the leaders of Judah who had assembled in Jerusalem for fear of Shishak, and he said to them, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says, ‘You have abandoned me; therefore, I now abandon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11443L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11443L\"></sup> you to Shishak.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The leaders of Israel and the king humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11444M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11444M\"></sup> themselves and said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is just.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11444N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11444N\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that they humbled themselves, this word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Shemaiah: “Since they have humbled themselves, I will not destroy them but will soon give them deliverance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11445O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11445O\"></sup> My wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11445P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11445P\"></sup> will not be poured out on Jerusalem through Shishak.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They will, however, become subject<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11446Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11446Q\"></sup> to him, so that they may learn the difference between serving me and serving the kings of other lands.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Shishak king of Egypt attacked Jerusalem, he carried off the treasures of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the treasures of the royal palace. He took everything, including the gold shields<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11447R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11447R\"></sup> Solomon had made.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So King Rehoboam made bronze shields to replace them and assigned these to the commanders of the guard on duty at the entrance to the royal palace.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Whenever the king went to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple, the guards went with him, bearing the shields, and afterward they returned them to the guardroom.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Because Rehoboam humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11450S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11450S\"></sup> himself, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger turned from him, and he was not totally destroyed. Indeed, there was some good<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11450T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11450T\"></sup> in Judah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>King Rehoboam established<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11451U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11451U\"></sup> himself firmly in Jerusalem and continued as king. He was forty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel in which to put his Name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11451V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11451V\"></sup> His mother’s name was Naamah; she was an Ammonite.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He did evil because he had not set his heart on seeking the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As for the events of Rehoboam’s reign, from beginning to end, are they not written in the records of Shemaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11453W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11453W\"></sup> the prophet and of Iddo the seer that deal with genealogies? There was continual warfare between Rehoboam and Jeroboam.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Rehoboam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11454X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11454X\"></sup> rested with his ancestors and was buried in the City of David. And Abijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11454Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11454Y\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>In the eighteenth year of the reign of Jeroboam, Abijah became king of Judah,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he reigned in Jerusalem three years. His mother’s name was Maakah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11456B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11456B\"></sup> a daughter of Uriel of Gibeah.There was war between Abijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11456C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11456C\"></sup> and Jeroboam.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11456D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11456D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abijah went into battle with an army of four hundred thousand able fighting men, and Jeroboam drew up a battle line against him with eight hundred thousand able troops.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Abijah stood on Mount Zemaraim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11458E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11458E\"></sup> in the hill country of Ephraim, and said, “Jeroboam and all Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11458F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11458F\"></sup> listen to me!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Don’t you know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, has given the kingship of Israel to David and his descendants forever<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11459G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11459G\"></sup> by a covenant of salt?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11459H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11459H\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Yet Jeroboam son of Nebat, an official of Solomon son of David, rebelled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11460I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11460I\"></sup> against his master.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Some worthless scoundrels<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11461J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11461J\"></sup> gathered around him and opposed Rehoboam son of Solomon when he was young and indecisive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11461K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11461K\"></sup> and not strong enough to resist them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“And now you plan to resist the kingdom of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which is in the hands of David’s descendants.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11462L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11462L\"></sup> You are indeed a vast army and have with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11462M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11462M\"></sup> the golden calves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11462N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11462N\"></sup> that Jeroboam made to be your gods.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But didn’t you drive out the priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11463O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11463O\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11463P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11463P\"></sup> the sons of Aaron, and the Levites, and make priests of your own as the peoples of other lands do? Whoever comes to consecrate himself with a young bull<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11463Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11463Q\"></sup> and seven rams<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11463R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11463R\"></sup> may become a priest of what are not gods.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11463S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11463S\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“As for us, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is our God, and we have not forsaken him. The priests who serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are sons of Aaron, and the Levites assist them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Every morning and evening<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11465T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11465T\"></sup> they present burnt offerings and fragrant incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11465U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11465U\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. They set out the bread on the ceremonially clean table<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11465V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11465V\"></sup> and light the lamps<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11465W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11465W\"></sup> on the gold lampstand every evening. We are observing the requirements of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God. But you have forsaken him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>God is with us; he is our leader. His priests with their trumpets will sound the battle cry against you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11466X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11466X\"></sup> People of Israel, do not fight against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11466Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11466Y\"></sup> the God of your ancestors, for you will not succeed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11466Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11466Z\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now Jeroboam had sent troops around to the rear, so that while he was in front of Judah the ambush<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11467AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11467AA\"></sup> was behind them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Judah turned and saw that they were being attacked at both front and rear. Then they cried out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11468AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11468AB\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The priests blew their trumpets",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the men of Judah raised the battle cry. At the sound of their battle cry, God routed Jeroboam and all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11469AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11469AC\"></sup> before Abijah and Judah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The Israelites fled before Judah, and God delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11470AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11470AD\"></sup> them into their hands.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Abijah and his troops inflicted heavy losses on them, so that there were five hundred thousand casualties among Israel’s able men.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Israelites were subdued on that occasion, and the people of Judah were victorious because they relied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11472AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11472AE\"></sup> on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Abijah pursued Jeroboam and took from him the towns of Bethel, Jeshanah and Ephron, with their surrounding villages.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jeroboam did not regain power during the time of Abijah. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck him down and he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Abijah grew in strength. He married fourteen wives and had twenty-two sons and sixteen daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The other events of Abijah’s reign, what he did and what he said, are written in the annotations of the prophet Iddo."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>And Abijah rested with his ancestors and was buried in the City of David. Asa his son succeeded him as king, and in his days the country was at peace for ten years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Asa did what was good and right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11478B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11478B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He removed the foreign altars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11479C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11479C\"></sup> and the high places, smashed the sacred stones<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11479D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11479D\"></sup> and cut down the Asherah poles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11479E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11479E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He commanded Judah to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11480F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11480F\"></sup> the God of their ancestors, and to obey his laws and commands.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He removed the high places<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11481G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11481G\"></sup> and incense altars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11481H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11481H\"></sup> in every town in Judah, and the kingdom was at peace under him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He built up the fortified cities of Judah, since the land was at peace. No one was at war with him during those years, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave him rest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11482I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11482I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Let us build up these towns,” he said to Judah, “and put walls around them, with towers, gates and bars. The land is still ours, because we have sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God; we sought him and he has given us rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11483J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11483J\"></sup> on every side.” So they built and prospered.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Asa had an army of three hundred thousand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11484K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11484K\"></sup> men from Judah, equipped with large shields and with spears, and two hundred and eighty thousand from Benjamin, armed with small shields and with bows. All these were brave fighting men.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Zerah the Cushite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11485L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11485L\"></sup> marched out against them with an army of thousands upon thousands and three hundred chariots, and came as far as Mareshah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11485M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11485M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Asa went out to meet him, and they took up battle positions in the Valley of Zephathah near Mareshah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Asa called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11487N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11487N\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God and said, “<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, there is no one like you to help the powerless against the mighty. Help us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11487O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11487O\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, for we rely<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11487P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11487P\"></sup> on you, and in your name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11487Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11487Q\"></sup> we have come against this vast army. <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you are our God; do not let mere mortals prevail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11487R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11487R\"></sup> against you.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11488S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11488S\"></sup> the Cushites before Asa and Judah. The Cushites fled,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Asa and his army pursued them as far as Gerar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11489T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11489T\"></sup> Such a great number of Cushites fell that they could not recover; they were crushed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11489U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11489U\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and his forces. The men of Judah carried off a large amount of plunder.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11489V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11489V\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They destroyed all the villages around Gerar, for the terror<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11490W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11490W\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had fallen on them. They looted all these villages, since there was much plunder there.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They also attacked the camps of the herders and carried off droves of sheep and goats and camels. Then they returned to Jerusalem."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>The Spirit of God came on<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11492B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11492B\"></sup> Azariah son of Oded.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He went out to meet Asa and said to him, “Listen to me, Asa and all Judah and Benjamin. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11493C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11493C\"></sup> when you are with him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11493D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11493D\"></sup> If you seek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11493E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11493E\"></sup> him, he will be found by you, but if you forsake him, he will forsake you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11493F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11493F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For a long time Israel was without the true God, without a priest to teach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11494G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11494G\"></sup> and without the law.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11494H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11494H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But in their distress they turned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, and sought him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11495I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11495I\"></sup> and he was found by them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In those days it was not safe to travel about,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11496J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11496J\"></sup> for all the inhabitants of the lands were in great turmoil.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>One nation was being crushed by another and one city by another,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11497K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11497K\"></sup> because God was troubling them with every kind of distress.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But as for you, be strong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11498L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11498L\"></sup> and do not give up, for your work will be rewarded.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11498M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11498M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Asa heard these words and the prophecy of Azariah son of Oded the prophet, he took courage. He removed the detestable idols<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11499N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11499N\"></sup> from the whole land of Judah and Benjamin and from the towns he had captured<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11499O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11499O\"></sup> in the hills of Ephraim. He repaired the altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11499P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11499P\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that was in front of the portico of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he assembled all Judah and Benjamin and the people from Ephraim, Manasseh and Simeon who had settled among them, for large numbers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11500Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11500Q\"></sup> had come over to him from Israel when they saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God was with him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>They assembled at Jerusalem in the third month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11501R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11501R\"></sup> of the fifteenth year of Asa’s reign.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>At that time they sacrificed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> seven hundred head of cattle and seven thousand sheep and goats from the plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11502S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11502S\"></sup> they had brought back.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They entered into a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11503T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11503T\"></sup> to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11503U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11503U\"></sup> the God of their ancestors, with all their heart and soul.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>All who would not seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, were to be put to death,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11504V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11504V\"></sup> whether small or great, man or woman.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They took an oath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with loud acclamation, with shouting and with trumpets and horns.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>All Judah rejoiced about the oath because they had sworn it wholeheartedly. They sought God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11506W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11506W\"></sup> eagerly, and he was found by them. So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11506X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11506X\"></sup> on every side.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>King Asa also deposed his grandmother Maakah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11507Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11507Y\"></sup> from her position as queen mother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11507Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11507Z\"></sup> because she had made a repulsive image for the worship of Asherah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11507AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11507AA\"></sup> Asa cut it down, broke it up and burned it in the Kidron Valley.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11507AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11507AB\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Although he did not remove the high places from Israel, Asa’s heart was fully committed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all his life.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He brought into the temple of God the silver and gold and the articles that he and his father had dedicated.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11509AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11509AC\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>There was no more war until the thirty-fifth year of Asa’s reign."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>In the thirty-sixth year of Asa’s reign Baasha<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11511C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11511C\"></sup> king of Israel went up against Judah and fortified Ramah to prevent anyone from leaving or entering the territory of Asa king of Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Asa then took the silver and gold out of the treasuries of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple and of his own palace and sent it to Ben-Hadad king of Aram, who was ruling in Damascus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11512D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11512D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Let there be a treaty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11513E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11513E\"></sup> between me and you,” he said, “as there was between my father and your father. See, I am sending you silver and gold. Now break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel so he will withdraw from me.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Ben-Hadad agreed with King Asa and sent the commanders of his forces against the towns of Israel. They conquered Ijon, Dan, Abel Maim and all the store cities of Naphtali.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11514F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11514F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Baasha heard this, he stopped building Ramah and abandoned his work.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then King Asa brought all the men of Judah, and they carried away from Ramah the stones and timber Baasha had been using. With them he built up Geba and Mizpah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11516G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11516G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>At that time Hanani<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11517H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11517H\"></sup> the seer came to Asa king of Judah and said to him: “Because you relied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11517I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11517I\"></sup> on the king of Aram and not on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, the army of the king of Aram has escaped from your hand.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Were not the Cushites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11518J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11518J\"></sup> and Libyans a mighty army with great numbers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11518K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11518K\"></sup> of chariots and horsemen? Yet when you relied on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he delivered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11518L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11518L\"></sup> them into your hand.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For the eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11519M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11519M\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> range throughout the earth to strengthen those whose hearts are fully committed to him. You have done a foolish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11519N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11519N\"></sup> thing, and from now on you will be at war.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11519O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11519O\"></sup>”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Asa was angry with the seer because of this; he was so enraged that he put him in prison.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11520P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11520P\"></sup> At the same time Asa brutally oppressed some of the people.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The events of Asa’s reign, from beginning to end, are written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In the thirty-ninth year of his reign Asa was afflicted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11522Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11522Q\"></sup> with a disease in his feet. Though his disease was severe, even in his illness he did not seek<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11522R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11522R\"></sup> help from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11522S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11522S\"></sup> but only from the physicians.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then in the forty-first year of his reign Asa died and rested with his ancestors.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They buried him in the tomb that he had cut out for himself<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11524T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11524T\"></sup> in the City of David. They laid him on a bier covered with spices and various blended perfumes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11524U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11524U\"></sup> and they made a huge fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11524V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11524V\"></sup> in his honor."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Jehoshaphat his son succeeded him as king and strengthened<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11525A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11525A\"></sup> himself against Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He stationed troops in all the fortified cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11526B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11526B\"></sup> of Judah and put garrisons in Judah and in the towns of Ephraim that his father Asa had captured.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11526C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Jehoshaphat because he followed the ways of his father David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11527D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11527D\"></sup> before him. He did not consult the Baals",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>but sought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11528E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11528E\"></sup> the God of his father and followed his commands rather than the practices of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> established the kingdom under his control; and all Judah brought gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11529F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11529F\"></sup> to Jehoshaphat, so that he had great wealth and honor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11529G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11529G\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>His heart was devoted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11530H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11530H\"></sup> to the ways of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; furthermore, he removed the high places<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11530I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11530I\"></sup> and the Asherah poles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11530J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11530J\"></sup> from Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11530K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11530K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In the third year of his reign he sent his officials Ben-Hail, Obadiah, Zechariah, Nethanel and Micaiah to teach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11531L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11531L\"></sup> in the towns of Judah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>With them were certain Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11532M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11532M\"></sup>—Shemaiah, Nethaniah, Zebadiah, Asahel, Shemiramoth, Jehonathan, Adonijah, Tobijah and Tob-Adonijah—and the priests Elishama and Jehoram.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They taught throughout Judah, taking with them the Book of the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11533N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11533N\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they went around to all the towns of Judah and taught the people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11534O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11534O\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> fell on all the kingdoms of the lands surrounding Judah, so that they did not go to war against Jehoshaphat.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Some Philistines brought Jehoshaphat gifts and silver as tribute, and the Arabs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11535P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11535P\"></sup> brought him flocks:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11535Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11535Q\"></sup> seven thousand seven hundred rams and seven thousand seven hundred goats.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jehoshaphat became more and more powerful; he built forts and store cities in Judah",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and had large supplies in the towns of Judah. He also kept experienced fighting men in Jerusalem.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Their enrollment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11538R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11538R\"></sup> by families was as follows:From Judah, commanders of units of 1,000:Adnah the commander, with 300,000 fighting men;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>next, Jehohanan the commander, with 280,000;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>next, Amasiah son of Zikri, who volunteered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11540S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11540S\"></sup> himself for the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with 200,000.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>From Benjamin:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11541T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11541T\"></sup>Eliada, a valiant soldier, with 200,000 men armed with bows and shields;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>next, Jehozabad, with 180,000 men armed for battle.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These were the men who served the king, besides those he stationed in the fortified cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11543U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11543U\"></sup> throughout Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11543V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11543V\"></sup>"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now Jehoshaphat had great wealth and honor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11544B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11544B\"></sup> and he allied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11544C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11544C\"></sup> himself with Ahab<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11544D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11544D\"></sup> by marriage.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Some years later he went down to see Ahab in Samaria. Ahab slaughtered many sheep and cattle for him and the people with him and urged him to attack Ramoth Gilead.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Ahab king of Israel asked Jehoshaphat king of Judah, “Will you go with me against Ramoth Gilead?”Jehoshaphat replied, “I am as you are, and my people as your people; we will join you in the war.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But Jehoshaphat also said to the king of Israel, “First seek the counsel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the king of Israel brought together the prophets—four hundred men—and asked them, “Shall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or shall I not?”“Go,” they answered, “for God will give it into the king’s hand.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Jehoshaphat asked, “Is there no longer a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> here whom we can inquire of?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king of Israel answered Jehoshaphat, “There is still one prophet through whom we can inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but I hate him because he never prophesies anything good about me, but always bad. He is Micaiah son of Imlah.”“The king should not say such a thing,” Jehoshaphat replied.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the king of Israel called one of his officials and said, “Bring Micaiah son of Imlah at once.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Dressed in their royal robes, the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah were sitting on their thrones at the threshing floor by the entrance of the gate of Samaria, with all the prophets prophesying before them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Zedekiah son of Kenaanah had made iron horns, and he declared, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: ‘With these you will gore the Arameans until they are destroyed.’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All the other prophets were prophesying the same thing. “Attack Ramoth Gilead<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11554E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11554E\"></sup> and be victorious,” they said, “for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give it into the king’s hand.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The messenger who had gone to summon Micaiah said to him, “Look, the other prophets without exception are predicting success for the king. Let your word agree with theirs, and speak favorably.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Micaiah said, “As surely as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, I can tell him only what my God says.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11556F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11556F\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When he arrived, the king asked him, “Micaiah, shall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or shall I not?”“Attack and be victorious,” he answered, “for they will be given into your hand.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The king said to him, “How many times must I make you swear to tell me nothing but the truth in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Micaiah answered, “I saw all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11559G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11559G\"></sup> scattered on the hills like sheep without a shepherd,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11559H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11559H\"></sup> and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘These people have no master. Let each one go home in peace.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “Didn’t I tell you that he never prophesies anything good about me, but only bad?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Micaiah continued, “Therefore hear the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: I saw the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sitting on his throne<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11561I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11561I\"></sup> with all the multitudes of heaven standing on his right and on his left.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, ‘Who will entice Ahab king of Israel into attacking Ramoth Gilead and going to his death there?’“One suggested this, and another that.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Finally, a spirit came forward, stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, ‘I will entice him.’“‘By what means?’ the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> asked.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“‘I will go and be a deceiving spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11564J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11564J\"></sup> in the mouths of all his prophets,’ he said.“‘You will succeed in enticing him,’ said the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. ‘Go and do it.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“So now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put a deceiving spirit in the mouths of these prophets of yours.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11565K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11565K\"></sup> The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has decreed disaster for you.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Zedekiah son of Kenaanah went up and slapped<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11566L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11566L\"></sup> Micaiah in the face. “Which way did the spirit from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> go when he went from me to speak to you?” he asked.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Micaiah replied, “You will find out on the day you go to hide in an inner room.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The king of Israel then ordered, “Take Micaiah and send him back to Amon the ruler of the city and to Joash the king’s son,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and say, ‘This is what the king says: Put this fellow in prison<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11569M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11569M\"></sup> and give him nothing but bread and water until I return safely.’”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Micaiah declared, “If you ever return safely, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not spoken through me.” Then he added, “Mark my words, all you people!”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah went up to Ramoth Gilead.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, “I will enter the battle in disguise, but you wear your royal robes.” So the king of Israel disguised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11572O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11572O\"></sup> himself and went into battle.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now the king of Aram had ordered his chariot commanders, “Do not fight with anyone, small or great, except the king of Israel.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When the chariot commanders saw Jehoshaphat, they thought, “This is the king of Israel.” So they turned to attack him, but Jehoshaphat cried out,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11574P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11574P\"></sup> and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helped him. God drew them away from him,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>for when the chariot commanders saw that he was not the king of Israel, they stopped pursuing him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But someone drew his bow at random and hit the king of Israel between the breastplate and the scale armor. The king told the chariot driver, “Wheel around and get me out of the fighting. I’ve been wounded.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>All day long the battle raged, and the king of Israel propped himself up in his chariot facing the Arameans until evening. Then at sunset he died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11577Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11577Q\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>When Jehoshaphat king of Judah returned safely to his palace in Jerusalem,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jehu<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11579A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11579A\"></sup> the seer, the son of Hanani, went out to meet him and said to the king, “Should you help the wicked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11579B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11579B\"></sup> and love those who hate the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11579C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11579C\"></sup> Because of this, the wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11579D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11579D\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is on you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>There is, however, some good<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11580E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11580E\"></sup> in you, for you have rid the land of the Asherah poles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11580F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11580F\"></sup> and have set your heart on seeking God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11580G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11580G\"></sup>”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jehoshaphat lived in Jerusalem, and he went out again among the people from Beersheba to the hill country of Ephraim and turned them back to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He appointed judges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11582H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11582H\"></sup> in the land, in each of the fortified cities of Judah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He told them, “Consider carefully what you do,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11583I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11583I\"></sup> because you are not judging for mere mortals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11583J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11583J\"></sup> but for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who is with you whenever you give a verdict.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now let the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be on you. Judge carefully, for with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God there is no injustice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11584K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11584K\"></sup> or partiality<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11584L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11584L\"></sup> or bribery.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In Jerusalem also, Jehoshaphat appointed some of the Levites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11585M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11585M\"></sup> priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11585N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11585N\"></sup> and heads of Israelite families to administer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11585O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11585O\"></sup> the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to settle disputes. And they lived in Jerusalem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He gave them these orders: “You must serve faithfully and wholeheartedly in the fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In every case that comes before you from your people who live in the cities—whether bloodshed or other concerns of the law, commands, decrees or regulations—you are to warn them not to sin against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11587P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11587P\"></sup> otherwise his wrath will come on you and your people. Do this, and you will not sin.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Amariah the chief priest will be over you in any matter concerning the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and Zebadiah son of Ishmael, the leader of the tribe of Judah, will be over you in any matter concerning the king, and the Levites will serve as officials before you. Act with courage,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11588Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11588Q\"></sup> and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with those who do well.”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>After this, the Moabites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11589A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11589A\"></sup> and Ammonites with some of the Meunites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11589B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11589B\"></sup> came to wage war against Jehoshaphat.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Some people came and told Jehoshaphat, “A vast army<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11590C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11590C\"></sup> is coming against you from Edom, from the other side of the Dead Sea. It is already in Hazezon Tamar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11590D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11590D\"></sup>” (that is, En Gedi).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11590E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11590E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Alarmed, Jehoshaphat resolved to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he proclaimed a fast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11591F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11591F\"></sup> for all Judah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The people of Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11592G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11592G\"></sup> came together to seek help from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; indeed, they came from every town in Judah to seek him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jehoshaphat stood up in the assembly of Judah and Jerusalem at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the front of the new courtyard",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and said:“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of our ancestors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11594H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11594H\"></sup> are you not the God who is in heaven?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11594I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11594I\"></sup> You rule over all the kingdoms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11594J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11594J\"></sup> of the nations. Power and might are in your hand, and no one can withstand you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11594K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11594K\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Our God, did you not drive out the inhabitants of this land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11595L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11595L\"></sup> before your people Israel and give it forever to the descendants of Abraham your friend?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11595M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11595M\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They have lived in it and have built in it a sanctuary<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11596N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11596N\"></sup> for your Name, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>‘If calamity comes upon us, whether the sword of judgment, or plague or famine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11597O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11597O\"></sup> we will stand in your presence before this temple that bears your Name and will cry out to you in our distress, and you will hear us and save us.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“But now here are men from Ammon, Moab and Mount Seir, whose territory you would not allow Israel to invade when they came from Egypt;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11598P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11598P\"></sup> so they turned away from them and did not destroy them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>See how they are repaying us by coming to drive us out of the possession<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11599Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11599Q\"></sup> you gave us as an inheritance.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Our God, will you not judge them?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11600R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11600R\"></sup> For we have no power to face this vast army that is attacking us. We do not know what to do, but our eyes are on you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11600S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11600S\"></sup>”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>All the men of Judah, with their wives and children and little ones, stood there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11602T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11602T\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came on Jahaziel son of Zechariah, the son of Benaiah, the son of Jeiel, the son of Mattaniah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11602U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11602U\"></sup> a Levite and descendant of Asaph, as he stood in the assembly.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said: “Listen, King Jehoshaphat and all who live in Judah and Jerusalem! This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says to you: ‘Do not be afraid or discouraged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11603V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11603V\"></sup> because of this vast army. For the battle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11603W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11603W\"></sup> is not yours, but God’s.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Tomorrow march down against them. They will be climbing up by the Pass of Ziz, and you will find them at the end of the gorge in the Desert of Jeruel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You will not have to fight this battle. Take up your positions; stand firm and see<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11605X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11605X\"></sup> the deliverance the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give you, Judah and Jerusalem. Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged. Go out to face them tomorrow, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be with you.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jehoshaphat bowed down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11606Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11606Y\"></sup> with his face to the ground, and all the people of Judah and Jerusalem fell down in worship before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then some Levites from the Kohathites and Korahites stood up and praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, with a very loud voice.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Early in the morning they left for the Desert of Tekoa. As they set out, Jehoshaphat stood and said, “Listen to me, Judah and people of Jerusalem! Have faith<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11608Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11608Z\"></sup> in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and you will be upheld; have faith in his prophets and you will be successful.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11608AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11608AA\"></sup>”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After consulting the people, Jehoshaphat appointed men to sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to praise him for the splendor of his holiness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11609AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11609AB\"></sup> as they went out at the head of the army, saying:“Give thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,for his love endures forever.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11609AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11609AC\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>As they began to sing and praise, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set ambushes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11610AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11610AD\"></sup> against the men of Ammon and Moab and Mount Seir who were invading Judah, and they were defeated.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11611AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11611AE\"></sup> and Moabites rose up against the men from Mount Seir<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11611AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11611AF\"></sup> to destroy and annihilate them. After they finished slaughtering the men from Seir, they helped to destroy one another.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11611AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11611AG\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When the men of Judah came to the place that overlooks the desert and looked toward the vast army, they saw only dead bodies lying on the ground; no one had escaped.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So Jehoshaphat and his men went to carry off their plunder, and they found among them a great amount of equipment and clothing and also articles of value—more than they could take away. There was so much plunder that it took three days to collect it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>On the fourth day they assembled in the Valley of Berakah, where they praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. This is why it is called the Valley of Berakah to this day.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then, led by Jehoshaphat, all the men of Judah and Jerusalem returned joyfully to Jerusalem, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given them cause to rejoice over their enemies.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They entered Jerusalem and went to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with harps and lyres and trumpets.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11617AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11617AH\"></sup> of God came on all the surrounding kingdoms when they heard how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had fought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11617AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11617AI\"></sup> against the enemies of Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the kingdom of Jehoshaphat was at peace, for his God had given him rest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11618AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11618AJ\"></sup> on every side.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So Jehoshaphat reigned over Judah. He was thirty-five years old when he became king of Judah, and he reigned in Jerusalem twenty-five years. His mother’s name was Azubah daughter of Shilhi.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He followed the ways of his father Asa and did not stray from them; he did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The high places,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11621AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11621AL\"></sup> however, were not removed, and the people still had not set their hearts on the God of their ancestors.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The other events of Jehoshaphat’s reign, from beginning to end, are written in the annals of Jehu<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11622AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11622AM\"></sup> son of Hanani, which are recorded in the book of the kings of Israel.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Later, Jehoshaphat king of Judah made an alliance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11623AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11623AN\"></sup> with Ahaziah king of Israel, whose ways were wicked.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11623AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11623AO\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He agreed with him to construct a fleet of trading ships. After these were built at Ezion Geber,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Eliezer son of Dodavahu of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat, saying, “Because you have made an alliance with Ahaziah, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will destroy what you have made.” The ships<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11625AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11625AP\"></sup> were wrecked and were not able to set sail to trade."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Then Jehoshaphat rested with his ancestors and was buried with them in the City of David. And Jehoram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11626A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11626A\"></sup> his son succeeded him as king.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jehoram’s brothers, the sons of Jehoshaphat, were Azariah, Jehiel, Zechariah, Azariahu, Michael and Shephatiah. All these were sons of Jehoshaphat king of Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Their father had given them many gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11628B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11628B\"></sup> of silver and gold and articles of value, as well as fortified cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11628C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11628C\"></sup> in Judah, but he had given the kingdom to Jehoram because he was his firstborn son.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When Jehoram established<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11629E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11629E\"></sup> himself firmly over his father’s kingdom, he put all his brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11629F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11629F\"></sup> to the sword along with some of the officials of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Jehoram was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eight years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He followed the ways of the kings of Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11631G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11631G\"></sup> as the house of Ahab had done, for he married a daughter of Ahab.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11631H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11631H\"></sup> He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nevertheless, because of the covenant the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made with David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11632I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11632I\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was not willing to destroy the house of David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11632J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11632J\"></sup> He had promised to maintain a lamp<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11632K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11632K\"></sup> for him and his descendants forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the time of Jehoram, Edom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11633L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11633L\"></sup> rebelled against Judah and set up its own king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Jehoram went there with his officers and all his chariots. The Edomites surrounded him and his chariot commanders, but he rose up and broke through by night.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>To this day Edom has been in rebellion against Judah.Libnah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11635M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11635M\"></sup> revolted at the same time, because Jehoram had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his ancestors.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He had also built high places on the hills of Judah and had caused the people of Jerusalem to prostitute themselves and had led Judah astray.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jehoram received a letter from Elijah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11637N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11637N\"></sup> the prophet, which said:“This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11637O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11637O\"></sup> David, says: ‘You have not followed the ways of your father Jehoshaphat or of Asa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11637P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11637P\"></sup> king of Judah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But you have followed the ways of the kings of Israel, and you have led Judah and the people of Jerusalem to prostitute themselves, just as the house of Ahab did.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11638Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11638Q\"></sup> You have also murdered your own brothers, members of your own family, men who were better<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11638R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11638R\"></sup> than you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is about to strike your people, your sons, your wives and everything that is yours, with a heavy blow.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You yourself will be very ill with a lingering disease<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11640S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11640S\"></sup> of the bowels, until the disease causes your bowels to come out.’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> aroused against Jehoram the hostility of the Philistines and of the Arabs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11641T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11641T\"></sup> who lived near the Cushites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They attacked Judah, invaded it and carried off all the goods found in the king’s palace, together with his sons and wives. Not a son was left to him except Ahaziah, the youngest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11642U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11642U\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>After all this, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> afflicted Jehoram with an incurable disease of the bowels.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>In the course of time, at the end of the second year, his bowels came out because of the disease, and he died in great pain. His people made no funeral fire in his honor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11644V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11644V\"></sup> as they had for his predecessors.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jehoram was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eight years. He passed away, to no one’s regret, and was buried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11645W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11645W\"></sup> in the City of David, but not in the tombs of the kings."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>The people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11646C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11646C\"></sup> of Jerusalem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11646D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11646D\"></sup> made Ahaziah, Jehoram’s youngest son, king in his place, since the raiders,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11646E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11646E\"></sup> who came with the Arabs into the camp, had killed all the older sons. So Ahaziah son of Jehoram king of Judah began to reign.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem one year. His mother’s name was Athaliah, a granddaughter of Omri.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He too followed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11648F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11648F\"></sup> the ways of the house of Ahab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11648G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11648G\"></sup> for his mother encouraged him to act wickedly.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the house of Ahab had done, for after his father’s death they became his advisers, to his undoing.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He also followed their counsel when he went with Joram son of Ahab king of Israel to wage war against Hazael king of Aram at Ramoth Gilead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11650H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11650H\"></sup> The Arameans wounded Joram;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>so he returned to Jezreel to recover from the wounds they had inflicted on him at Ramoth in his battle with Hazael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11651I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11651I\"></sup> king of Aram.Then Ahaziah son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to Jezreel to see Joram son of Ahab because he had been wounded.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Through Ahaziah’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11652J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11652J\"></sup> visit to Joram, God brought about Ahaziah’s downfall. When Ahaziah arrived, he went out with Joram to meet Jehu son of Nimshi, whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had anointed to destroy the house of Ahab.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>While Jehu was executing judgment on the house of Ahab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11653K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11653K\"></sup> he found the officials of Judah and the sons of Ahaziah’s relatives, who had been attending Ahaziah, and he killed them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He then went in search of Ahaziah, and his men captured him while he was hiding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11654L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11654L\"></sup> in Samaria. He was brought to Jehu and put to death. They buried him, for they said, “He was a son of Jehoshaphat, who sought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11654M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11654M\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all his heart.” So there was no one in the house of Ahaziah powerful enough to retain the kingdom.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she proceeded to destroy the whole royal family of the house of Judah.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Jehoram, took Joash son of Ahaziah and stole him away from among the royal princes who were about to be murdered and put him and his nurse in a bedroom. Because Jehosheba, the daughter of King Jehoram and wife of the priest Jehoiada, was Ahaziah’s sister, she hid the child from Athaliah so she could not kill him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He remained hidden with them at the temple of God for six years while Athaliah ruled the land."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>In the seventh year Jehoiada showed his strength. He made a covenant with the commanders of units of a hundred: Azariah son of Jeroham, Ishmael son of Jehohanan, Azariah son of Obed, Maaseiah son of Adaiah, and Elishaphat son of Zikri.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They went throughout Judah and gathered the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11659A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11659A\"></sup> and the heads of Israelite families from all the towns. When they came to Jerusalem,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the whole assembly made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11660B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11660B\"></sup> with the king at the temple of God.Jehoiada said to them, “The king’s son shall reign, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> promised concerning the descendants of David.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11660C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11660C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now this is what you are to do: A third of you priests and Levites who are going on duty on the Sabbath are to keep watch at the doors,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>a third of you at the royal palace and a third at the Foundation Gate, and all the others are to be in the courtyards of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>No one is to enter the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> except the priests and Levites on duty; they may enter because they are consecrated, but all the others are to observe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11663D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11663D\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s command not to enter.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Levites are to station themselves around the king, each with weapon in hand. Anyone who enters the temple is to be put to death. Stay close to the king wherever he goes.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Levites and all the men of Judah did just as Jehoiada the priest ordered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11665E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11665E\"></sup> Each one took his men—those who were going on duty on the Sabbath and those who were going off duty—for Jehoiada the priest had not released any of the divisions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11665F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11665F\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he gave the commanders of units of a hundred the spears and the large and small shields that had belonged to King David and that were in the temple of God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He stationed all the men, each with his weapon in his hand, around the king—near the altar and the temple, from the south side to the north side of the temple.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jehoiada and his sons brought out the king’s son and put the crown on him; they presented him with a copy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11668G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11668G\"></sup> of the covenant and proclaimed him king. They anointed him and shouted, “Long live the king!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and cheering the king, she went to them at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>She looked, and there was the king,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11670H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11670H\"></sup> standing by his pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11670I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11670I\"></sup> at the entrance. The officers and the trumpeters were beside the king, and all the people of the land were rejoicing and blowing trumpets, and musicians with their instruments were leading the praises. Then Athaliah tore her robes and shouted, “Treason! Treason!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jehoiada the priest sent out the commanders of units of a hundred, who were in charge of the troops, and said to them: “Bring her out between the ranks and put to the sword anyone who follows her.” For the priest had said, “Do not put her to death at the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they seized her as she reached the entrance of the Horse Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11672J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11672J\"></sup> on the palace grounds, and there they put her to death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jehoiada then made a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11673K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11673K\"></sup> that he, the people and the king would be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All the people went to the temple of Baal and tore it down. They smashed the altars and idols and killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11674L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11674L\"></sup> Mattan the priest of Baal in front of the altars.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Jehoiada placed the oversight of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the hands of the Levitical priests,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11675M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11675M\"></sup> to whom David had made assignments in the temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11675N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11675N\"></sup> to present the burnt offerings of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as written in the Law of Moses, with rejoicing and singing, as David had ordered.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He also stationed gatekeepers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11676O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11676O\"></sup> at the gates of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple so that no one who was in any way unclean might enter.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He took with him the commanders of hundreds, the nobles, the rulers of the people and all the people of the land and brought the king down from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. They went into the palace through the Upper Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11677P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11677P\"></sup> and seated the king on the royal throne.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>All the people of the land rejoiced, and the city was calm, because Athaliah had been slain with the sword.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11678Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11678Q\"></sup>"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Joash was seven years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem forty years. His mother’s name was Zibiah; she was from Beersheba.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joash did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11680C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11680C\"></sup> all the years of Jehoiada the priest.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jehoiada chose two wives for him, and he had sons and daughters.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Some time later Joash decided to restore the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He called together the priests and Levites and said to them, “Go to the towns of Judah and collect the money<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11683D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11683D\"></sup> due annually from all Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11683E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11683E\"></sup> to repair the temple of your God. Do it now.” But the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11683F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11683F\"></sup> did not act at once.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Therefore the king summoned Jehoiada the chief priest and said to him, “Why haven’t you required the Levites to bring in from Judah and Jerusalem the tax imposed by Moses the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and by the assembly of Israel for the tent of the covenant law?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11684G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11684G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now the sons of that wicked woman Athaliah had broken into the temple of God and had used even its sacred objects for the Baals.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>At the king’s command, a chest was made and placed outside, at the gate of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>A proclamation was then issued in Judah and Jerusalem that they should bring to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the tax that Moses the servant of God had required of Israel in the wilderness.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>All the officials and all the people brought their contributions gladly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11688H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11688H\"></sup> dropping them into the chest until it was full.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Whenever the chest was brought in by the Levites to the king’s officials and they saw that there was a large amount of money, the royal secretary and the officer of the chief priest would come and empty the chest and carry it back to its place. They did this regularly and collected a great amount of money.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The king and Jehoiada gave it to those who carried out the work required for the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. They hired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11690I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11690I\"></sup> masons and carpenters to restore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple, and also workers in iron and bronze to repair the temple.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The men in charge of the work were diligent, and the repairs progressed under them. They rebuilt the temple of God according to its original design and reinforced it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When they had finished, they brought the rest of the money to the king and Jehoiada, and with it were made articles for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple: articles for the service and for the burnt offerings, and also dishes and other objects of gold and silver. As long as Jehoiada lived, burnt offerings were presented continually in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now Jehoiada was old and full of years, and he died at the age of a hundred and thirty.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He was buried with the kings in the City of David, because of the good he had done in Israel for God and his temple.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After the death of Jehoiada, the officials of Judah came and paid homage to the king, and he listened to them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They abandoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11696J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11696J\"></sup> the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors, and worshiped Asherah poles and idols.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11696K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11696K\"></sup> Because of their guilt, God’s anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11696L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11696L\"></sup> came on Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Although the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent prophets to the people to bring them back to him, and though they testified against them, they would not listen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11697M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11697M\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11698N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11698N\"></sup> of God came on Zechariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11698O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11698O\"></sup> son of Jehoiada the priest. He stood before the people and said, “This is what God says: ‘Why do you disobey the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s commands? You will not prosper.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11698P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11698P\"></sup> Because you have forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, he has forsaken<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11698Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11698Q\"></sup> you.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But they plotted against him, and by order of the king they stoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11699R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11699R\"></sup> him to death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11699S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11699S\"></sup> in the courtyard of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11699T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11699T\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>King Joash did not remember the kindness Zechariah’s father Jehoiada had shown him but killed his son, who said as he lay dying, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> see this and call you to account.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11700U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11700U\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>At the turn of the year, the army of Aram marched against Joash; it invaded Judah and Jerusalem and killed all the leaders of the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11701V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11701V\"></sup> They sent all the plunder to their king in Damascus.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Although the Aramean army had come with only a few men,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11702W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11702W\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered into their hands a much larger army.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11702X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11702X\"></sup> Because Judah had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors, judgment was executed on Joash.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When the Arameans withdrew, they left Joash severely wounded. His officials conspired against him for murdering the son of Jehoiada the priest, and they killed him in his bed. So he died and was buried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11703Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11703Y\"></sup> in the City of David, but not in the tombs of the kings.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Those who conspired against him were Zabad, son of Shimeath an Ammonite woman, and Jehozabad, son of Shimrith<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11704Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11704Z\"></sup> a Moabite woman.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11704AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11704AA\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The account of his sons, the many prophecies about him, and the record of the restoration of the temple of God are written in the annotations on the book of the kings. And Amaziah his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Amaziah was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem twenty-nine years. His mother’s name was Jehoaddan; she was from Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but not wholeheartedly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11707D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11707D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>After the kingdom was firmly in his control, he executed the officials who had murdered his father the king.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Yet he did not put their children to death, but acted in accordance with what is written in the Law, in the Book of Moses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11709E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11709E\"></sup> where the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded: “Parents shall not be put to death for their children, nor children be put to death for their parents; each will die for their own sin.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11709F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11709F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Amaziah called the people of Judah together and assigned them according to their families to commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds for all Judah and Benjamin. He then mustered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11710G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11710G\"></sup> those twenty years old<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11710H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11710H\"></sup> or more and found that there were three hundred thousand men fit for military service,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11710I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11710I\"></sup> able to handle the spear and shield.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He also hired a hundred thousand fighting men from Israel for a hundred talents of silver.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But a man of God came to him and said, “Your Majesty, these troops from Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11712J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11712J\"></sup> must not march with you, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is not with Israel—not with any of the people of Ephraim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Even if you go and fight courageously in battle, God will overthrow you before the enemy, for God has the power to help or to overthrow.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11713K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11713K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Amaziah asked the man of God, “But what about the hundred talents I paid for these Israelite troops?”The man of God replied, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> can give you much more than that.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11714L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11714L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Amaziah dismissed the troops who had come to him from Ephraim and sent them home. They were furious with Judah and left for home in a great rage.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11715M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11715M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Amaziah then marshaled his strength and led his army to the Valley of Salt, where he killed ten thousand men of Seir.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The army of Judah also captured ten thousand men alive, took them to the top of a cliff and threw them down so that all were dashed to pieces.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11717N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11717N\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Meanwhile the troops that Amaziah had sent back and had not allowed to take part in the war raided towns belonging to Judah from Samaria to Beth Horon. They killed three thousand people and carried off great quantities of plunder.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Amaziah returned from slaughtering the Edomites, he brought back the gods of the people of Seir. He set them up as his own gods,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11719O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11719O\"></sup> bowed down to them and burned sacrifices to them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Amaziah, and he sent a prophet to him, who said, “Why do you consult this people’s gods, which could not save<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11720P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11720P\"></sup> their own people from your hand?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>While he was still speaking, the king said to him, “Have we appointed you an adviser to the king? Stop! Why be struck down?”So the prophet stopped but said, “I know that God has determined to destroy you, because you have done this and have not listened to my counsel.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After Amaziah king of Judah consulted his advisers, he sent this challenge to Jehoash son of Jehoahaz, the son of Jehu, king of Israel: “Come, let us face each other in battle.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But Jehoash king of Israel replied to Amaziah king of Judah: “A thistle<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11723Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11723Q\"></sup> in Lebanon sent a message to a cedar in Lebanon, ‘Give your daughter to my son in marriage.’ Then a wild beast in Lebanon came along and trampled the thistle underfoot.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You say to yourself that you have defeated Edom, and now you are arrogant and proud. But stay at home! Why ask for trouble and cause your own downfall and that of Judah also?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Amaziah, however, would not listen, for God so worked that he might deliver them into the hands of Jehoash, because they sought the gods of Edom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11725R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11725R\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Jehoash king of Israel attacked. He and Amaziah king of Judah faced each other at Beth Shemesh in Judah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Judah was routed by Israel, and every man fled to his home.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Joash, the son of Ahaziah, at Beth Shemesh. Then Jehoash brought him to Jerusalem and broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the Ephraim Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11728S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11728S\"></sup> to the Corner Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11728T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11728T\"></sup>—a section about four hundred cubits long.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He took all the gold and silver and all the articles found in the temple of God that had been in the care of Obed-Edom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11729U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11729U\"></sup> together with the palace treasures and the hostages, and returned to Samaria.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Amaziah son of Joash king of Judah lived for fifteen years after the death of Jehoash son of Jehoahaz king of Israel.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>As for the other events of Amaziah’s reign, from beginning to end, are they not written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>From the time that Amaziah turned away from following the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, they conspired against him in Jerusalem and he fled to Lachish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11732V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11732V\"></sup>, but they sent men after him to Lachish and killed him there.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He was brought back by horse and was buried with his ancestors in the City of Judah."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>Then all the people of Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11734C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11734C\"></sup> took Uzziah, who was sixteen years old, and made him king in place of his father Amaziah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was the one who rebuilt Elath and restored it to Judah after Amaziah rested with his ancestors.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Uzziah was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem fifty-two years. His mother’s name was Jekoliah; she was from Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his father Amaziah had done.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He sought God during the days of Zechariah, who instructed him in the fear of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11738D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11738D\"></sup> As long as he sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, God gave him success.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11738E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11738E\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He went to war against the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11739F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11739F\"></sup> and broke down the walls of Gath, Jabneh and Ashdod.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11739G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11739G\"></sup> He then rebuilt towns near Ashdod and elsewhere among the Philistines.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>God helped him against the Philistines and against the Arabs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11740H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11740H\"></sup> who lived in Gur Baal and against the Meunites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11740I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11740I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11741J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11741J\"></sup> brought tribute to Uzziah, and his fame spread as far as the border of Egypt, because he had become very powerful.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at the Corner Gate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11742K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11742K\"></sup> at the Valley Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11742L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11742L\"></sup> and at the angle of the wall, and he fortified them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He also built towers in the wilderness and dug many cisterns, because he had much livestock in the foothills and in the plain. He had people working his fields and vineyards in the hills and in the fertile lands, for he loved the soil.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Uzziah had a well-trained army, ready to go out by divisions according to their numbers as mustered by Jeiel the secretary and Maaseiah the officer under the direction of Hananiah, one of the royal officials.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The total number of family leaders over the fighting men was 2,600.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Under their command was an army of 307,500 men trained for war, a powerful force to support the king against his enemies.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Uzziah provided shields, spears, helmets, coats of armor, bows and slingstones for the entire army.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11747M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11747M\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In Jerusalem he made devices invented for use on the towers and on the corner defenses so that soldiers could shoot arrows and hurl large stones from the walls. His fame spread far and wide, for he was greatly helped until he became powerful.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But after Uzziah became powerful, his pride<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11749N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11749N\"></sup> led to his downfall.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11749O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11749O\"></sup> He was unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11749P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11749P\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, and entered the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to burn incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11749Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11749Q\"></sup> on the altar of incense.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Azariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11750R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11750R\"></sup> the priest with eighty other courageous priests of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> followed him in.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They confronted King Uzziah and said, “It is not right for you, Uzziah, to burn incense to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. That is for the priests,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11751S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11751S\"></sup> the descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11751T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11751T\"></sup> of Aaron,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11751U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11751U\"></sup> who have been consecrated to burn incense.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11751V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11751V\"></sup> Leave the sanctuary, for you have been unfaithful; and you will not be honored by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Uzziah, who had a censer in his hand ready to burn incense, became angry. While he was raging at the priests in their presence before the incense altar in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple, leprosy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11752W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11752W\"></sup> broke out on his forehead.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Azariah the chief priest and all the other priests looked at him, they saw that he had leprosy on his forehead, so they hurried him out. Indeed, he himself was eager to leave, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had afflicted him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>King Uzziah had leprosy until the day he died. He lived in a separate house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11754X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11754X\"></sup>—leprous, and banned from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Jotham his son had charge of the palace and governed the people of the land.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The other events of Uzziah’s reign, from beginning to end, are recorded by the prophet Isaiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11755Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11755Y\"></sup> son of Amoz.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Uzziah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11756Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11756Z\"></sup> rested with his ancestors and was buried near them in a cemetery that belonged to the kings, for people said, “He had leprosy.” And Jotham his son succeeded him as king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11756AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11756AA\"></sup>"
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Jotham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11757B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11757B\"></sup> was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem sixteen years. His mother’s name was Jerusha daughter of Zadok.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his father Uzziah had done, but unlike him he did not enter the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The people, however, continued their corrupt practices.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jotham rebuilt the Upper Gate of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did extensive work on the wall at the hill of Ophel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11759C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11759C\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He built towns in the hill country of Judah and forts and towers in the wooded areas.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Jotham waged war against the king of the Ammonites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11761D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11761D\"></sup> and conquered them. That year the Ammonites paid him a hundred talents of silver, ten thousand cors of wheat and ten thousand cors of barley. The Ammonites brought him the same amount also in the second and third years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jotham grew powerful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11762E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11762E\"></sup> because he walked steadfastly before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The other events in Jotham’s reign, including all his wars and the other things he did, are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem sixteen years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jotham rested with his ancestors and was buried in the City of David. And Ahaz his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>Ahaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11766B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11766B\"></sup> was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem sixteen years. Unlike David his father, he did not do what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He followed the ways of the kings of Israel and also made idols<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11767C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11767C\"></sup> for worshiping the Baals.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He burned sacrifices in the Valley of Ben Hinnom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11768D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11768D\"></sup> and sacrificed his children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11768E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11768E\"></sup> in the fire, engaging in the detestable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11768F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11768F\"></sup> practices of the nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before the Israelites.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He offered sacrifices and burned incense at the high places, on the hilltops and under every spreading tree.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God delivered him into the hands of the king of Aram.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11770G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11770G\"></sup> The Arameans defeated him and took many of his people as prisoners and brought them to Damascus.He was also given into the hands of the king of Israel, who inflicted heavy casualties on him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In one day Pekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11771H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11771H\"></sup> son of Remaliah killed a hundred and twenty thousand soldiers in Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11771I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11771I\"></sup>—because Judah had forsaken the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Zikri, an Ephraimite warrior, killed Maaseiah the king’s son, Azrikam the officer in charge of the palace, and Elkanah, second to the king.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The men of Israel took captive from their fellow Israelites who were from Judah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11773J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11773J\"></sup> two hundred thousand wives, sons and daughters. They also took a great deal of plunder, which they carried back to Samaria.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11773K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11773K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But a prophet of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> named Oded was there, and he went out to meet the army when it returned to Samaria. He said to them, “Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your ancestors, was angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11774L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11774L\"></sup> with Judah, he gave them into your hand. But you have slaughtered them in a rage that reaches to heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11774M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11774M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And now you intend to make the men and women of Judah and Jerusalem your slaves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11775N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11775N\"></sup> But aren’t you also guilty of sins against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now listen to me! Send back your fellow Israelites you have taken as prisoners, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s fierce anger rests on you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11776O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11776O\"></sup>”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then some of the leaders in Ephraim—Azariah son of Jehohanan, Berekiah son of Meshillemoth, Jehizkiah son of Shallum, and Amasa son of Hadlai—confronted those who were arriving from the war.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“You must not bring those prisoners here,” they said, “or we will be guilty before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Do you intend to add to our sin and guilt? For our guilt is already great, and his fierce anger rests on Israel.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the soldiers gave up the prisoners and plunder in the presence of the officials and all the assembly.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The men designated by name took the prisoners, and from the plunder they clothed all who were naked. They provided them with clothes and sandals, food and drink,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11780P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11780P\"></sup> and healing balm. All those who were weak they put on donkeys. So they took them back to their fellow Israelites at Jericho, the City of Palms,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11780Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11780Q\"></sup> and returned to Samaria.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11780R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11780R\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At that time King Ahaz sent to the kings of Assyria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11781S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11781S\"></sup> for help.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The Edomites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11782T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11782T\"></sup> had again come and attacked Judah and carried away prisoners,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11782U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11782U\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>while the Philistines<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11783V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11783V\"></sup> had raided towns in the foothills and in the Negev of Judah. They captured and occupied Beth Shemesh, Aijalon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11783W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11783W\"></sup> and Gederoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11783X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11783X\"></sup> as well as Soko,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11783Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11783Y\"></sup> Timnah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11783Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11783Z\"></sup> and Gimzo, with their surrounding villages.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had humbled Judah because of Ahaz king of Israel, for he had promoted wickedness in Judah and had been most unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11784AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11784AA\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Tiglath-Pileser<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11785AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11785AB\"></sup> king of Assyria<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11785AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11785AC\"></sup> came to him, but he gave him trouble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11785AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11785AD\"></sup> instead of help.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11785AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11785AE\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Ahaz<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11786AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11786AF\"></sup> took some of the things from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and from the royal palace and from the officials and presented them to the king of Assyria, but that did not help him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11786AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11786AG\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>In his time of trouble King Ahaz became even more unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11787AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11787AH\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He offered sacrifices to the gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11788AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11788AI\"></sup> of Damascus, who had defeated him; for he thought, “Since the gods of the kings of Aram have helped them, I will sacrifice to them so they will help me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11788AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11788AJ\"></sup> But they were his downfall and the downfall of all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11788AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11788AK\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Ahaz gathered together the furnishings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11789AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11789AL\"></sup> from the temple of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11789AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11789AM\"></sup> and cut them in pieces. He shut the doors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11789AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11789AN\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple and set up altars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11789AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11789AO\"></sup> at every street corner in Jerusalem.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>In every town in Judah he built high places to burn sacrifices to other gods and aroused the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of his ancestors.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The other events of his reign and all his ways, from beginning to end, are written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Ahaz rested<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11792AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11792AP\"></sup> with his ancestors and was buried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11792AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11792AQ\"></sup> in the city of Jerusalem, but he was not placed in the tombs of the kings of Israel. And Hezekiah his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Hezekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11793B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11793B\"></sup> was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem twenty-nine years. His mother’s name was Abijah daughter of Zechariah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as his father David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11794C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11794C\"></sup> had done.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the first month of the first year of his reign, he opened the doors of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and repaired<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11795D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11795D\"></sup> them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He brought in the priests and the Levites, assembled them in the square on the east side",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and said: “Listen to me, Levites! Consecrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11797E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11797E\"></sup> yourselves now and consecrate the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your ancestors. Remove all defilement from the sanctuary.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Our parents<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11798F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11798F\"></sup> were unfaithful;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11798G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11798G\"></sup> they did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God and forsook him. They turned their faces away from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s dwelling place and turned their backs on him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They also shut the doors of the portico and put out the lamps. They did not burn incense<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11799H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11799H\"></sup> or present any burnt offerings at the sanctuary to the God of Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Therefore, the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has fallen on Judah and Jerusalem; he has made them an object of dread and horror<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11800I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11800I\"></sup> and scorn,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11800J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11800J\"></sup> as you can see with your own eyes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>This is why our fathers have fallen by the sword and why our sons and daughters and our wives are in captivity.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11801K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11801K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now I intend to make a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11802L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11802L\"></sup> with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, so that his fierce anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11802M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11802M\"></sup> will turn away from us.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My sons, do not be negligent now, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has chosen you to stand before him and serve him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11803N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11803N\"></sup> to minister<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11803O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11803O\"></sup> before him and to burn incense.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then these Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11804P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11804P\"></sup> set to work:from the Kohathites,Mahath son of Amasai and Joel son of Azariah;from the Merarites,Kish son of Abdi and Azariah son of Jehallelel;from the Gershonites,Joah son of Zimmah and Eden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11804Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11804Q\"></sup> son of Joah;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>from the descendants of Elizaphan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11805R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11805R\"></sup>Shimri and Jeiel;from the descendants of Asaph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11805S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11805S\"></sup>Zechariah and Mattaniah;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>from the descendants of Heman,Jehiel and Shimei;from the descendants of Jeduthun,Shemaiah and Uzziel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When they had assembled their fellow Levites and consecrated themselves, they went in to purify<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11807T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11807T\"></sup> the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as the king had ordered, following the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The priests went into the sanctuary of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to purify it. They brought out to the courtyard of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple everything unclean that they found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. The Levites took it and carried it out to the Kidron Valley.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11808U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11808U\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They began the consecration on the first day of the first month, and by the eighth day of the month they reached the portico of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. For eight more days they consecrated the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> itself, finishing on the sixteenth day of the first month.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they went in to King Hezekiah and reported: “We have purified the entire temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and the table for setting out the consecrated bread, with all its articles.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>We have prepared and consecrated all the articles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11811V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11811V\"></sup> that King Ahaz removed in his unfaithfulness while he was king. They are now in front of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s altar.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Early the next morning King Hezekiah gathered the city officials together and went up to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They brought seven bulls, seven rams, seven male lambs and seven male goats<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11813W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11813W\"></sup> as a sin offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11813X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11813X\"></sup> for the kingdom, for the sanctuary and for Judah. The king commanded the priests, the descendants of Aaron, to offer these on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they slaughtered the bulls, and the priests took the blood and splashed it against the altar; next they slaughtered the rams and splashed their blood against the altar; then they slaughtered the lambs and splashed their blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11814Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11814Y\"></sup> against the altar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The goats<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11815Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11815Z\"></sup> for the sin offering were brought before the king and the assembly, and they laid their hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11815AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11815AA\"></sup> on them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The priests then slaughtered the goats and presented their blood on the altar for a sin offering to atone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11816AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11816AB\"></sup> for all Israel, because the king had ordered the burnt offering and the sin offering for all Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11816AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11816AC\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He stationed the Levites in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with cymbals, harps and lyres in the way prescribed by David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11817AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11817AD\"></sup> and Gad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11817AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11817AE\"></sup> the king’s seer and Nathan the prophet; this was commanded by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> through his prophets.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So the Levites stood ready with David’s instruments,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11818AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11818AF\"></sup> and the priests with their trumpets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11818AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11818AG\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Hezekiah gave the order to sacrifice the burnt offering on the altar. As the offering began, singing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began also, accompanied by trumpets and the instruments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11819AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11819AH\"></sup> of David king of Israel.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The whole assembly bowed in worship, while the musicians played and the trumpets sounded. All this continued until the sacrifice of the burnt offering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11820AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11820AI\"></sup> was completed.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When the offerings were finished, the king and everyone present with him knelt down and worshiped.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11821AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11821AJ\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>King Hezekiah and his officials ordered the Levites to praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with the words of David and of Asaph the seer. So they sang praises with gladness and bowed down and worshiped.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Hezekiah said, “You have now dedicated yourselves to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Come and bring sacrifices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11823AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11823AK\"></sup> and thank offerings to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” So the assembly brought sacrifices and thank offerings, and all whose hearts were willing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11823AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11823AL\"></sup> brought burnt offerings.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The number of burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11824AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11824AM\"></sup> the assembly brought was seventy bulls, a hundred rams and two hundred male lambs—all of them for burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The animals consecrated as sacrifices amounted to six hundred bulls and three thousand sheep and goats.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The priests, however, were too few to skin all the burnt offerings;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11826AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11826AN\"></sup> so their relatives the Levites helped them until the task was finished and until other priests had been consecrated,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11826AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11826AO\"></sup> for the Levites had been more conscientious in consecrating themselves than the priests had been.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>There were burnt offerings in abundance, together with the fat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11827AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11827AP\"></sup> of the fellowship offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11827AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11827AQ\"></sup> and the drink offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11827AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11827AR\"></sup> that accompanied the burnt offerings.So the service of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was reestablished.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Hezekiah and all the people rejoiced at what God had brought about for his people, because it was done so quickly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11828AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11828AS\"></sup>"
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>Hezekiah sent word to all Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11829A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11829A\"></sup> and Judah and also wrote letters to Ephraim and Manasseh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11829B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11829B\"></sup> inviting them to come to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem and celebrate the Passover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11829C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11829C\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king and his officials and the whole assembly in Jerusalem decided to celebrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11830D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11830D\"></sup> the Passover in the second month.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They had not been able to celebrate it at the regular time because not enough priests had consecrated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11831E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11831E\"></sup> themselves and the people had not assembled in Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The plan seemed right both to the king and to the whole assembly.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They decided to send a proclamation throughout Israel, from Beersheba to Dan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11833F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11833F\"></sup> calling the people to come to Jerusalem and celebrate the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel. It had not been celebrated in large numbers according to what was written.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>At the king’s command, couriers went throughout Israel and Judah with letters from the king and from his officials, which read:“People of Israel, return to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Abraham, Isaac and Israel, that he may return to you who are left, who have escaped from the hand of the kings of Assyria.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Do not be like your parents<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11835G\"></sup> and your fellow Israelites, who were unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11835H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11835H\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors, so that he made them an object of horror,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11835I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11835I\"></sup> as you see.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Do not be stiff-necked,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11836J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11836J\"></sup> as your ancestors were; submit to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Come to his sanctuary, which he has consecrated forever. Serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, so that his fierce anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11836K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11836K\"></sup> will turn away from you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If you return<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11837L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11837L\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then your fellow Israelites and your children will be shown compassion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11837M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11837M\"></sup> by their captors and will return to this land, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God is gracious and compassionate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11837N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11837N\"></sup> He will not turn his face from you if you return to him.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The couriers went from town to town in Ephraim and Manasseh, as far as Zebulun, but people scorned and ridiculed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11838O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11838O\"></sup> them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Nevertheless, some from Asher, Manasseh and Zebulun humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11839P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11839P\"></sup> themselves and went to Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11839Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11839Q\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Also in Judah the hand of God was on the people to give them unity<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11840R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11840R\"></sup> of mind to carry out what the king and his officials had ordered, following the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A very large crowd of people assembled in Jerusalem to celebrate the Festival of Unleavened Bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11841S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11841S\"></sup> in the second month.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They removed the altars<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11842T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11842T\"></sup> in Jerusalem and cleared away the incense altars and threw them into the Kidron Valley.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11842U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11842U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They slaughtered the Passover lamb on the fourteenth day of the second month. The priests and the Levites were ashamed and consecrated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11843V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11843V\"></sup> themselves and brought burnt offerings to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then they took up their regular positions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11844W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11844W\"></sup> as prescribed in the Law of Moses the man of God. The priests splashed against the altar the blood handed to them by the Levites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Since many in the crowd had not consecrated themselves, the Levites had to kill<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11845X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11845X\"></sup> the Passover lambs for all those who were not ceremonially clean and could not consecrate their lambs to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Although most of the many people who came from Ephraim, Manasseh, Issachar and Zebulun had not purified themselves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11846Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11846Y\"></sup> yet they ate the Passover, contrary to what was written. But Hezekiah prayed for them, saying, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who is good, pardon everyone",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>who sets their heart on seeking God—the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors—even if they are not clean according to the rules of the sanctuary.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> heard<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11848Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11848Z\"></sup> Hezekiah and healed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11848AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11848AA\"></sup> the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11848AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11848AB\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The Israelites who were present in Jerusalem celebrated the Festival of Unleavened Bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11849AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11849AC\"></sup> for seven days with great rejoicing, while the Levites and priests praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> every day with resounding instruments dedicated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Hezekiah spoke encouragingly to all the Levites, who showed good understanding of the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. For the seven days they ate their assigned portion and offered fellowship offerings and praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The whole assembly then agreed to celebrate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11851AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11851AD\"></sup> the festival seven more days; so for another seven days they celebrated joyfully.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hezekiah king of Judah provided<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11852AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11852AE\"></sup> a thousand bulls and seven thousand sheep and goats for the assembly, and the officials provided them with a thousand bulls and ten thousand sheep and goats. A great number of priests consecrated themselves.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The entire assembly of Judah rejoiced, along with the priests and Levites and all who had assembled from Israel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11853AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11853AF\"></sup>, including the foreigners who had come from Israel and also those who resided in Judah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>There was great joy in Jerusalem, for since the days of Solomon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11854AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11854AG\"></sup> son of David king of Israel there had been nothing like this in Jerusalem.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The priests and the Levites stood to bless<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11855AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11855AH\"></sup> the people, and God heard them, for their prayer reached heaven, his holy dwelling place."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>When all this had ended, the Israelites who were there went out to the towns of Judah, smashed the sacred stones and cut down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11856A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11856A\"></sup> the Asherah poles. They destroyed the high places and the altars throughout Judah and Benjamin and in Ephraim and Manasseh. After they had destroyed all of them, the Israelites returned to their own towns and to their own property.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Hezekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11857C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11857C\"></sup> assigned the priests and Levites to divisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11857D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11857D\"></sup>—each of them according to their duties as priests or Levites—to offer burnt offerings and fellowship offerings, to minister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11857E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11857E\"></sup> to give thanks and to sing praises<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11857F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11857F\"></sup> at the gates of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s dwelling.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11857G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11857G\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king contributed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11858H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11858H\"></sup> from his own possessions for the morning and evening burnt offerings and for the burnt offerings on the Sabbaths, at the New Moons and at the appointed festivals as written in the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11858I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11858I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He ordered the people living in Jerusalem to give the portion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11859J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11859J\"></sup> due the priests and Levites so they could devote themselves to the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As soon as the order went out, the Israelites generously gave the firstfruits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11860K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11860K\"></sup> of their grain, new wine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11860L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11860L\"></sup> olive oil and honey and all that the fields produced. They brought a great amount, a tithe of everything.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The people of Israel and Judah who lived in the towns of Judah also brought a tithe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11861M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11861M\"></sup> of their herds and flocks and a tithe of the holy things dedicated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, and they piled them in heaps.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11861N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11861N\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They began doing this in the third month and finished in the seventh month.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11862O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11862O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Hezekiah and his officials came and saw the heaps, they praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and blessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11863P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11863P\"></sup> his people Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Hezekiah asked the priests and Levites about the heaps;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and Azariah the chief priest, from the family of Zadok,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11865Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11865Q\"></sup> answered, “Since the people began to bring their contributions to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, we have had enough to eat and plenty to spare, because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed his people, and this great amount is left over.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11865R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11865R\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Hezekiah gave orders to prepare storerooms in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and this was done.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then they faithfully brought in the contributions, tithes and dedicated gifts. Konaniah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11867S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11867S\"></sup> a Levite, was the overseer in charge of these things, and his brother Shimei was next in rank.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jehiel, Azaziah, Nahath, Asahel, Jerimoth, Jozabad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11868T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11868T\"></sup> Eliel, Ismakiah, Mahath and Benaiah were assistants of Konaniah and Shimei his brother. All these served by appointment of King Hezekiah and Azariah the official in charge of the temple of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Kore son of Imnah the Levite, keeper of the East Gate, was in charge of the freewill offerings given to God, distributing the contributions made to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and also the consecrated gifts.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Eden,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11870U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11870U\"></sup> Miniamin, Jeshua, Shemaiah, Amariah and Shekaniah assisted him faithfully in the towns<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11870V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11870V\"></sup> of the priests, distributing to their fellow priests according to their divisions, old and young alike.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>In addition, they distributed to the males three years old or more whose names were in the genealogical records<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11871W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11871W\"></sup>—all who would enter the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to perform the daily duties of their various tasks, according to their responsibilities and their divisions.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they distributed to the priests enrolled by their families in the genealogical records and likewise to the Levites twenty years old or more, according to their responsibilities and their divisions.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They included all the little ones, the wives, and the sons and daughters of the whole community listed in these genealogical records. For they were faithful in consecrating themselves.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As for the priests, the descendants of Aaron, who lived on the farmlands around their towns or in any other towns,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11874X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11874X\"></sup> men were designated by name to distribute portions to every male among them and to all who were recorded in the genealogies of the Levites.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>This is what Hezekiah did throughout Judah, doing what was good and right and faithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11875Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11875Y\"></sup> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>In everything that he undertook in the service of God’s temple and in obedience to the law and the commands, he sought his God and worked wholeheartedly. And so he prospered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11876Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11876Z\"></sup>"
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>After all that Hezekiah had so faithfully done, Sennacherib<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11877C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11877C\"></sup> king of Assyria came and invaded Judah. He laid siege to the fortified cities, thinking to conquer them for himself.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib had come and that he intended to wage war against Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11878D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11878D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>he consulted with his officials and military staff about blocking off the water from the springs outside the city, and they helped him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They gathered a large group of people who blocked all the springs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11880E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11880E\"></sup> and the stream that flowed through the land. “Why should the kings of Assyria come and find plenty of water?” they said.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then he worked hard repairing all the broken sections of the wall<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11881F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11881F\"></sup> and building towers on it. He built another wall outside that one and reinforced the terraces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11881G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11881G\"></sup> of the City of David. He also made large numbers of weapons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11881H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11881H\"></sup> and shields.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He appointed military officers over the people and assembled them before him in the square at the city gate and encouraged them with these words:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Be strong and courageous.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11883I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11883I\"></sup> Do not be afraid or discouraged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11883J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11883J\"></sup> because of the king of Assyria and the vast army with him, for there is a greater power with us than with him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11883K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11883K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>With him is only the arm of flesh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11884L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11884L\"></sup> but with us<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11884M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11884M\"></sup> is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God to help us and to fight our battles.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11884N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11884N\"></sup> And the people gained confidence from what Hezekiah the king of Judah said.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Later, when Sennacherib king of Assyria and all his forces were laying siege to Lachish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11885O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11885O\"></sup> he sent his officers to Jerusalem with this message for Hezekiah king of Judah and for all the people of Judah who were there:",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“This is what Sennacherib king of Assyria says: On what are you basing your confidence,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11886P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11886P\"></sup> that you remain in Jerusalem under siege?",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When Hezekiah says, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God will save us from the hand of the king of Assyria,’ he is misleading<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11887Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11887Q\"></sup> you, to let you die of hunger and thirst.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Did not Hezekiah himself remove this god’s high places and altars, saying to Judah and Jerusalem, ‘You must worship before one altar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11888R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11888R\"></sup> and burn sacrifices on it’?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“Do you not know what I and my predecessors have done to all the peoples of the other lands? Were the gods of those nations ever able to deliver their land from my hand?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11889S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11889S\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Who of all the gods of these nations that my predecessors destroyed has been able to save his people from me? How then can your god deliver you from my hand?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now do not let Hezekiah deceive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11891T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11891T\"></sup> you and mislead you like this. Do not believe him, for no god of any nation or kingdom has been able to deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11891U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11891U\"></sup> his people from my hand or the hand of my predecessors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11891V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11891V\"></sup> How much less will your god deliver you from my hand!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Sennacherib’s officers spoke further against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God and against his servant Hezekiah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king also wrote letters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11893W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11893W\"></sup> ridiculing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11893X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11893X\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, and saying this against him: “Just as the gods<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11893Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11893Y\"></sup> of the peoples of the other lands did not rescue their people from my hand, so the god of Hezekiah will not rescue his people from my hand.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they called out in Hebrew to the people of Jerusalem who were on the wall, to terrify them and make them afraid in order to capture the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They spoke about the God of Jerusalem as they did about the gods of the other peoples of the world—the work of human hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11895Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11895Z\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>King Hezekiah and the prophet Isaiah son of Amoz cried out in prayer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11896AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11896AA\"></sup> to heaven about this.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent an angel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11897AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11897AB\"></sup> who annihilated all the fighting men and the commanders and officers in the camp of the Assyrian king. So he withdrew to his own land in disgrace. And when he went into the temple of his god, some of his sons, his own flesh and blood, cut him down with the sword.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11897AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11897AC\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saved Hezekiah and the people of Jerusalem from the hand of Sennacherib king of Assyria and from the hand of all others. He took care of them on every side.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Many brought offerings to Jerusalem for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and valuable gifts<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11899AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11899AD\"></sup> for Hezekiah king of Judah. From then on he was highly regarded by all the nations.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>In those days Hezekiah became ill and was at the point of death. He prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who answered him and gave him a miraculous sign.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11900AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11900AF\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Hezekiah’s heart was proud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11901AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11901AG\"></sup> and he did not respond to the kindness shown him; therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11901AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11901AH\"></sup> was on him and on Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Hezekiah repented<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11902AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11902AI\"></sup> of the pride of his heart, as did the people of Jerusalem; therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s wrath did not come on them during the days of Hezekiah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11902AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11902AJ\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Hezekiah had very great wealth and honor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11903AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11903AK\"></sup> and he made treasuries for his silver and gold and for his precious stones, spices, shields and all kinds of valuables.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He also made buildings to store the harvest of grain, new wine and olive oil; and he made stalls for various kinds of cattle, and pens for the flocks.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He built villages and acquired great numbers of flocks and herds, for God had given him very great riches.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11905AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11905AL\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It was Hezekiah who blocked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11906AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11906AM\"></sup> the upper outlet of the Gihon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11906AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11906AN\"></sup> spring and channeled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11906AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11906AO\"></sup> the water down to the west side of the City of David. He succeeded in everything he undertook.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But when envoys were sent by the rulers of Babylon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11907AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11907AP\"></sup> to ask him about the miraculous sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11907AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11907AQ\"></sup> that had occurred in the land, God left him to test<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11907AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11907AR\"></sup> him and to know everything that was in his heart.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The other events of Hezekiah’s reign and his acts of devotion are written in the vision of the prophet Isaiah son of Amoz in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Hezekiah rested with his ancestors and was buried on the hill where the tombs of David’s descendants are. All Judah and the people of Jerusalem honored him when he died. And Manasseh his son succeeded him as king."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>Manasseh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11910C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11910C\"></sup> was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem fifty-five years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11911D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11911D\"></sup> following the detestable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11911E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11911E\"></sup> practices of the nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had driven out before the Israelites.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He rebuilt the high places his father Hezekiah had demolished; he also erected altars to the Baals and made Asherah poles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11912F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11912F\"></sup> He bowed down<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11912G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11912G\"></sup> to all the starry hosts and worshiped them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He built altars in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, of which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said, “My Name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11913H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11913H\"></sup> will remain in Jerusalem forever.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In both courts of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11914I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11914I\"></sup> he built altars to all the starry hosts.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He sacrificed his children<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11915J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11915J\"></sup> in the fire in the Valley of Ben Hinnom, practiced divination and witchcraft, sought omens, and consulted mediums<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11915K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11915K\"></sup> and spiritists.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11915L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11915L\"></sup> He did much evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, arousing his anger.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He took the image he had made and put it in God’s temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11916M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11916M\"></sup> of which God had said to David and to his son Solomon, “In this temple and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, I will put my Name forever.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I will not again make the feet of the Israelites leave the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11917N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11917N\"></sup> I assigned to your ancestors, if only they will be careful to do everything I commanded them concerning all the laws, decrees and regulations given through Moses.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Manasseh led Judah and the people of Jerusalem astray, so that they did more evil than the nations the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had destroyed before the Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11918O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11918O\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Manasseh and his people, but they paid no attention.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought against them the army commanders of the king of Assyria, who took Manasseh prisoner,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11920P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11920P\"></sup> put a hook<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11920Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11920Q\"></sup> in his nose, bound him with bronze shackles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11920R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11920R\"></sup> and took him to Babylon.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In his distress he sought the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God and humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11921S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11921S\"></sup> himself greatly before the God of his ancestors.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And when he prayed to him, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was moved by his entreaty and listened to his plea; so he brought him back to Jerusalem and to his kingdom. Then Manasseh knew that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Afterward he rebuilt the outer wall of the City of David, west of the Gihon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11923T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11923T\"></sup> spring in the valley, as far as the entrance of the Fish Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11923U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11923U\"></sup> and encircling the hill of Ophel;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11923V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11923V\"></sup> he also made it much higher. He stationed military commanders in all the fortified cities in Judah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He got rid of the foreign gods and removed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11924W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11924W\"></sup> the image from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as well as all the altars he had built on the temple hill and in Jerusalem; and he threw them out of the city.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then he restored the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and sacrificed fellowship offerings and thank offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11925X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11925X\"></sup> on it, and told Judah to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The people, however, continued to sacrifice at the high places, but only to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The other events of Manasseh’s reign, including his prayer to his God and the words the seers spoke to him in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, are written in the annals of the kings of Israel.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>His prayer and how God was moved by his entreaty, as well as all his sins and unfaithfulness, and the sites where he built high places and set up Asherah poles and idols before he humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11928Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11928Y\"></sup> himself—all these are written in the records of the seers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11928Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11928Z\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Manasseh rested with his ancestors and was buried<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11929AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11929AA\"></sup> in his palace. And Amon his son succeeded him as king.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Amon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11930AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11930AC\"></sup> was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem two years.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as his father Manasseh had done. Amon worshiped and offered sacrifices to all the idols Manasseh had made.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But unlike his father Manasseh, he did not humble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11932AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11932AD\"></sup> himself before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; Amon increased his guilt.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Amon’s officials conspired against him and assassinated him in his palace.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11934AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11934AE\"></sup> of the land killed all who had plotted against King Amon, and they made Josiah his son king in his place."
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>Josiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11935D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11935D\"></sup> was eight years old when he became king,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11935E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11935E\"></sup> and he reigned in Jerusalem thirty-one years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He did what was right in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and followed the ways of his father David,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11936F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11936F\"></sup> not turning aside to the right or to the left.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the eighth year of his reign, while he was still young, he began to seek the God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11937G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11937G\"></sup> of his father David. In his twelfth year he began to purge Judah and Jerusalem of high places, Asherah poles and idols.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Under his direction the altars of the Baals were torn down; he cut to pieces the incense altars that were above them, and smashed the Asherah poles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11938H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11938H\"></sup> and the idols. These he broke to pieces and scattered over the graves of those who had sacrificed to them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11938I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11938I\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He burned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11939J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11939J\"></sup> the bones of the priests on their altars, and so he purged Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In the towns of Manasseh, Ephraim and Simeon, as far as Naphtali, and in the ruins around them,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>he tore down the altars and the Asherah poles and crushed the idols to powder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11941K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11941K\"></sup> and cut to pieces all the incense altars throughout Israel. Then he went back to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the eighteenth year of Josiah’s reign, to purify the land and the temple, he sent Shaphan son of Azaliah and Maaseiah the ruler of the city, with Joah son of Joahaz, the recorder, to repair the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They went to Hilkiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11943L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11943L\"></sup> the high priest and gave him the money that had been brought into the temple of God, which the Levites who were the gatekeepers had collected from the people of Manasseh, Ephraim and the entire remnant of Israel and from all the people of Judah and Benjamin and the inhabitants of Jerusalem.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then they entrusted it to the men appointed to supervise the work on the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple. These men paid the workers who repaired and restored the temple.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They also gave money<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11945M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11945M\"></sup> to the carpenters and builders to purchase dressed stone, and timber for joists and beams for the buildings that the kings of Judah had allowed to fall into ruin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11945N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11945N\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The workers labored faithfully.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11946O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11946O\"></sup> Over them to direct them were Jahath and Obadiah, Levites descended from Merari, and Zechariah and Meshullam, descended from Kohath. The Levites—all who were skilled in playing musical instruments—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11946P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11946P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>had charge of the laborers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11947Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11947Q\"></sup> and supervised all the workers from job to job. Some of the Levites were secretaries, scribes and gatekeepers.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>While they were bringing out the money that had been taken into the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, Hilkiah the priest found the Book of the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that had been given through Moses.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hilkiah said to Shaphan the secretary, “I have found the Book of the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11949T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11949T\"></sup> in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” He gave it to Shaphan.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Shaphan took the book to the king and reported to him: “Your officials are doing everything that has been committed to them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They have paid out the money that was in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and have entrusted it to the supervisors and workers.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Shaphan the secretary informed the king, “Hilkiah the priest has given me a book.” And Shaphan read from it in the presence of the king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When the king heard the words of the Law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11953U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11953U\"></sup> he tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11953V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11953V\"></sup> his robes.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He gave these orders to Hilkiah, Ahikam son of Shaphan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11954W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11954W\"></sup>, Abdon son of Micah, Shaphan the secretary and Asaiah the king’s attendant:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Go and inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for me and for the remnant in Israel and Judah about what is written in this book that has been found. Great is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s anger that is poured out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11955X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11955X\"></sup> on us because those who have gone before us have not kept the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; they have not acted in accordance with all that is written in this book.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Hilkiah and those the king had sent with him went to speak to the prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11956Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11956Y\"></sup> Huldah, who was the wife of Shallum son of Tokhath, the son of Hasrah, keeper of the wardrobe. She lived in Jerusalem, in the New Quarter.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>She said to them, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says: Tell the man who sent you to me,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says: I am going to bring disaster<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11958Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11958Z\"></sup> on this place and its people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11958AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11958AA\"></sup>—all the curses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11958AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11958AB\"></sup> written in the book that has been read in the presence of the king of Judah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Because they have forsaken me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11959AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11959AC\"></sup> and burned incense to other gods and aroused my anger by all that their hands have made, my anger will be poured out on this place and will not be quenched.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Tell the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, says concerning the words you heard:",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Because your heart was responsive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11961AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11961AD\"></sup> and you humbled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11961AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11961AE\"></sup> yourself before God when you heard what he spoke against this place and its people, and because you humbled yourself before me and tore your robes and wept in my presence, I have heard you, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now I will gather you to your ancestors,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11962AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11962AF\"></sup> and you will be buried in peace. Your eyes will not see all the disaster I am going to bring on this place and on those who live here.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11962AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11962AG\"></sup>So they took her answer back to the king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then the king called together all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He went up to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11964AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11964AH\"></sup> with the people of Judah, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the priests and the Levites—all the people from the least to the greatest. He read in their hearing all the words of the Book of the Covenant, which had been found in the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The king stood by his pillar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11965AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11965AI\"></sup> and renewed the covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11965AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11965AJ\"></sup> in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—to follow<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11965AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11965AK\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and keep his commands, statutes and decrees with all his heart and all his soul, and to obey the words of the covenant written in this book.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then he had everyone in Jerusalem and Benjamin pledge themselves to it; the people of Jerusalem did this in accordance with the covenant of God, the God of their ancestors.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Josiah removed all the detestable<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11967AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11967AL\"></sup> idols from all the territory belonging to the Israelites, and he had all who were present in Israel serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God. As long as he lived, they did not fail to follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors."
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>Josiah celebrated the Passover<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11968B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11968B\"></sup> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem, and the Passover lamb was slaughtered on the fourteenth day of the first month.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He appointed the priests to their duties and encouraged them in the service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He said to the Levites, who instructed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11970C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11970C\"></sup> all Israel and who had been consecrated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: “Put the sacred ark in the temple that Solomon son of David king of Israel built. It is not to be carried about on your shoulders. Now serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and his people Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Prepare yourselves by families in your divisions,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11971D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11971D\"></sup> according to the instructions written by David king of Israel and by his son Solomon.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Stand in the holy place with a group of Levites for each subdivision of the families of your fellow Israelites, the lay people.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Slaughter the Passover lambs, consecrate yourselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11973E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11973E\"></sup> and prepare the lambs for your fellow Israelites, doing what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded through Moses.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Josiah provided for all the lay people who were there a total of thirty thousand lambs and goats for the Passover offerings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11974F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11974F\"></sup> and also three thousand cattle—all from the king’s own possessions.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11974G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11974G\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His officials also contributed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11975H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11975H\"></sup> voluntarily to the people and the priests and Levites. Hilkiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11975I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11975I\"></sup> Zechariah and Jehiel, the officials in charge of God’s temple, gave the priests twenty-six hundred Passover offerings and three hundred cattle.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Also Konaniah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11976J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11976J\"></sup> along with Shemaiah and Nethanel, his brothers, and Hashabiah, Jeiel and Jozabad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11976K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11976K\"></sup> the leaders of the Levites, provided five thousand Passover offerings and five hundred head of cattle for the Levites.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The service was arranged and the priests stood in their places with the Levites in their divisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11977L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11977L\"></sup> as the king had ordered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11977M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11977M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The Passover lambs were slaughtered,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11978N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11978N\"></sup> and the priests splashed against the altar the blood handed to them, while the Levites skinned the animals.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They set aside the burnt offerings to give them to the subdivisions of the families of the people to offer to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as it is written in the Book of Moses. They did the same with the cattle.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They roasted the Passover animals over the fire as prescribed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11980O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11980O\"></sup> and boiled the holy offerings in pots, caldrons and pans and served them quickly to all the people.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After this, they made preparations for themselves and for the priests, because the priests, the descendants of Aaron, were sacrificing the burnt offerings and the fat portions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11981P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11981P\"></sup> until nightfall. So the Levites made preparations for themselves and for the Aaronic priests.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The musicians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11982Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11982Q\"></sup> the descendants of Asaph, were in the places prescribed by David, Asaph, Heman and Jeduthun the king’s seer. The gatekeepers at each gate did not need to leave their posts, because their fellow Levites made the preparations for them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So at that time the entire service of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was carried out for the celebration of the Passover and the offering of burnt offerings on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as King Josiah had ordered.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The Israelites who were present celebrated the Passover at that time and observed the Festival of Unleavened Bread for seven days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Passover had not been observed like this in Israel since the days of the prophet Samuel; and none of the kings of Israel had ever celebrated such a Passover as did Josiah, with the priests, the Levites and all Judah and Israel who were there with the people of Jerusalem.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>This Passover was celebrated in the eighteenth year of Josiah’s reign.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After all this, when Josiah had set the temple in order, Necho king of Egypt went up to fight at Carchemish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11987S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11987S\"></sup> on the Euphrates,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11987T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11987T\"></sup> and Josiah marched out to meet him in battle.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Necho sent messengers to him, saying, “What quarrel is there, king of Judah, between you and me? It is not you I am attacking at this time, but the house with which I am at war. God has told<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11988U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11988U\"></sup> me to hurry; so stop opposing God, who is with me, or he will destroy you.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Josiah, however, would not turn away from him, but disguised<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11989V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11989V\"></sup> himself to engage him in battle. He would not listen to what Necho had said at God’s command but went to fight him on the plain of Megiddo.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Archers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11990W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11990W\"></sup> shot King Josiah, and he told his officers, “Take me away; I am badly wounded.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So they took him out of his chariot, put him in his other chariot and brought him to Jerusalem, where he died. He was buried in the tombs of his ancestors, and all Judah and Jerusalem mourned for him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jeremiah composed laments for Josiah, and to this day all the male and female singers commemorate Josiah in the laments.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11992X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11992X\"></sup> These became a tradition in Israel and are written in the Laments.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11992Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11992Y\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The other events of Josiah’s reign and his acts of devotion in accordance with what is written in the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>all the events, from beginning to end, are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">36 </span><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>And the people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11995A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11995A\"></sup> of the land took Jehoahaz son of Josiah and made him king in Jerusalem in place of his father.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king of Egypt dethroned him in Jerusalem and imposed on Judah a levy of a hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king of Egypt made Eliakim, a brother of Jehoahaz, king over Judah and Jerusalem and changed Eliakim’s name to Jehoiakim. But Necho<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11998C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11998C\"></sup> took Eliakim’s brother Jehoahaz and carried him off to Egypt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11998D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11998D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Jehoiakim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-11999F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-11999F\"></sup> was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eleven years. He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12000G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12000G\"></sup> king of Babylon attacked him and bound him with bronze shackles to take him to Babylon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12000H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12000H\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar also took to Babylon articles from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and put them in his temple there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12001I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12001I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The other events of Jehoiakim’s reign, the detestable things he did and all that was found against him, are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah. And Jehoiachin his son succeeded him as king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jehoiachin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12003K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12003K\"></sup> was eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months and ten days. He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In the spring, King Nebuchadnezzar sent for him and brought him to Babylon,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12004L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12004L\"></sup> together with articles of value from the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he made Jehoiachin’s uncle, Zedekiah, king over Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Zedekiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12005N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12005N\"></sup> was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eleven years.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He did evil in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12006O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12006O\"></sup> his God and did not humble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12006P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12006P\"></sup> himself before Jeremiah the prophet, who spoke the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He also rebelled against King Nebuchadnezzar, who had made him take an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12007Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12007Q\"></sup> in God’s name. He became stiff-necked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12007R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12007R\"></sup> and hardened his heart and would not turn to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Furthermore, all the leaders of the priests and the people became more and more unfaithful,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12008S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12008S\"></sup> following all the detestable practices of the nations and defiling the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he had consecrated in Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their ancestors, sent word to them through his messengers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12009V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12009V\"></sup> again and again,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12009W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12009W\"></sup> because he had pity on his people and on his dwelling place.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But they mocked God’s messengers, despised his words and scoffed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12010X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12010X\"></sup> at his prophets until the wrath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12010Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12010Y\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was aroused against his people and there was no remedy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12010Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12010Z\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He brought up against them the king of the Babylonians,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12011AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12011AA\"></sup> who killed their young men with the sword in the sanctuary, and did not spare young men<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12011AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12011AB\"></sup> or young women, the elderly or the infirm.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12011AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12011AC\"></sup> God gave them all into the hands of Nebuchadnezzar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12011AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12011AD\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He carried to Babylon all the articles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12012AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12012AE\"></sup> from the temple of God, both large and small, and the treasures of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple and the treasures of the king and his officials.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They set fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12013AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12013AF\"></sup> to God’s temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12013AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12013AG\"></sup> and broke down the wall<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12013AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12013AH\"></sup> of Jerusalem; they burned all the palaces and destroyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12013AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12013AI\"></sup> everything of value there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12013AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12013AJ\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He carried into exile<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12014AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12014AK\"></sup> to Babylon the remnant, who escaped from the sword, and they became servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12014AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12014AL\"></sup> to him and his successors until the kingdom of Persia came to power.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The land enjoyed its sabbath rests;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12015AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12015AM\"></sup> all the time of its desolation it rested,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12015AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12015AN\"></sup> until the seventy years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12015AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12015AO\"></sup> were completed in fulfillment of the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken by Jeremiah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>In the first year of Cyrus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12016AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12016AP\"></sup> king of Persia, in order to fulfill the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken by Jeremiah, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> moved the heart of Cyrus king of Persia to make a proclamation throughout his realm and also to put it in writing:",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“This is what Cyrus king of Persia says:“‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, has given me all the kingdoms of the earth and he has appointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12017AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12017AQ\"></sup> me to build a temple for him at Jerusalem in Judah. Any of his people among you may go up, and may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God be with them.’”"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;